title: quick and easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in covered casserole.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: skipperlabskava
directions: Cut meat into 1/4-inch thick slices and pound slightly.
Cut potatoes into thick slices.
Heat the butter and saute the onions in it.
Add the meat slices and brown on both sides.
Remove to a plate and add the hot water, salt and pepper to the frying pan. Stir well.
Using a casserole dish, layer the meat and potatoes; add the liquid from the frying pan and then the beer.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
When ready to serve, sprinkle with parsley.

title: fantasy island
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° until brown, cool.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar, Cool Whip and vanilla and spread over crust mixture.
Mix pudding mixes with milk.
Spread over the cream cheese mixture.
Cover the top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine the Bisquick and margarine, then add the boiling water.
Form into a ball and spread over pie plate with your fingers.
Bake in 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Pour one-half the batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add egg noodles and soup with water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer until noodles are tender. (Add more water as needed.)

title: pork and apple pie
directions: Alternate layers of meat and apples in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan or Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle each layer of apples with sugar and cinnamon. Add gravy. Combine yams and butter and beat until smooth. Blend in cream.
Add salt and pepper. Spread over pork mixture. Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: swiss melt appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Mix olives, shredded Swiss and salad dressing.
Spread about a tablespoon of the mixture on each slice of bread.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and place on serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with whipped topping.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple.
Can add coconut.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Press crescent rolls into 9-inch pie pan. Brown ground beef, onion, oregano, basil, salt and pepper. Drain. Brown crescent rolls in pan for 3 to 5 minutes. Take pan out of oven. Mix tomato paste with hamburger mixture. Pour in pie shell. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: seafood bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole blend soup, milk and salad dressing.
Mix in all ingredients.
Sprinkle paprika on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Peel and slice thin carrot.
Cook until tender (crisp).
Cut bacon into bits.
Saute and remove from pan.
Saute diced onion in bacon drippings and then mix sugar, flour (cornstarch), vinegar and a little water.
Stir into pan with onions.
Mix and thicken. Pour over drained carrots and add bacon bit.
Mix and serve warm.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Place cake mix in a large mixing bowl.
Add flour, gelatin, water, oil and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with mixer. Add 1/2 strawberries and beat 1 minute longer.
Pour into greased cake pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool cake.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: In a large bowl, cut shortening into flour until completely mixed.
Into a smaller bowl, beat egg.
Add white vinegar and cold water.
Beat together.
Add liquid to flour mixture; blend until completely mixed.
Don't worry about overmixing.
Will be sticky. Place in refrigerator about 1/2 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Place oil and soy sauce in large skillet; brown steak.
Add 1 cup water and place lid on skillet.
Simmer for about 30 minutes. Stir cornstarch in 1 cup of water, mixing well.
Add to skillet; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; stir in onions and green pepper. Cook until crisp.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: golden nugget macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
In a large saucepan, saute onion in butter.
Add corn, salt and pepper; heat through.
Stir in cheese and macaroni.
Heat until cheese melts. If thinner consistency is desired, stir in 2 tablespoons of milk. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chili cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven according to biscuit can.
Cook hamburger completely.
Add onions and green pepper while cooking, if desired.
Add tomato sauce and paste. Then add chili powder to taste.
Mixture should be thick.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Separate biscuits by layer then spread thin layers to cover bottom of dish.
Layer hamburger-biscuits-cheese.
Bake 30 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown, then drain ground beef.
Pour cream of mushroom and cheese soup over meat that has been put in a casserole dish. Cover with Tater Tots and cook at 450° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all together and let stand overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add bread crumbs the last 20 minutes.

title: carry-along sardine sandwiches
directions: Mash sardines, including the oil, with the mayonnaise.
Stir in relish and celery.
Make 6 sandwiches of the filling and bread using about 1/4 cup filling for each, cut each in half.
Wrap individually and tightly and refrigerate until ready to pack into (vacuum bag) cooler.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Pour oil to a depth of 1/4 inch in a large skillet.

title: surprise barbecue ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in bag and place in baking pan.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and green pepper.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Place ribs in bag.
Turn bag to coat ribs with sauce.
Arrange ribs in even layer.
Close bag and make 6 slits in top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In 4-quart microproof bowl, cook sugar, milk and margarine for 20 to 22 minutes, stirring well every 5 minutes until soft ball forms in cold water. Stir in remaining ingredients in order listed. Beat until thick and pour into 9 x 12-inch buttered pan.

title: blueberry delight
directions: You will also need a 9 x 13 pan.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, no longer.

title: perfect tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Garnish with potato chips.
Bake in casserole dish at 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: gerry's colorado baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until done; remove and leave enough grease to cook onions, then add sugar and vinegar.
Drain all beans, except pork and beans.
Add crumbled bacon and all beans to mixture.

title: warm fruited brie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
On baking sheet, unfold 1 pie crust. Place Brie in center.
Turn under edge of pie crust to within 1/2-inch of cheese and flute edge.
Remove Brie.
Prick pie crust with fork.
Place baking sheet on center rack and bake 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Flour board.
Unfold 2nd pie crust.
Cut out 2-inch oval shaped leaves.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 5 minutes.
Cool.
Lower oven to 350°.
Put Brie on fluted pie crust.
Arrange apples around edge, grapes and raspberries in center.
Bake 10 minutes.
In saucepan, blend apple juice and cornstarch.
Bring to boil while stirring until clear and thick. Remove from heat.
Arrange pastry leaves on top of Brie.
Brush with cooked glaze.
Stand 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: frozen cauliflower tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti to desired doneness; drain.
Rinse with hot water to keep warm and set aside.
Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk and blend well.
Cook 6 to 10 minutes, until mixture thickens and boils, stirring constantly. Stir in chicken bouillon, thyme, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Spoon cooked spaghetti into greased pan.
Top with cooked vegetables.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake until thoroughly heated and bubbly.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate crescent dough into 2 long rectangles.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan; press dough to cover bottom of pan, sealing perforations.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and almond extract until smooth.
Spread over dough.
Spoon fruit filling evenly over cream cheese mixture.
Combine flour, brown sugar and margarine.
Mix until crumbly.
Stir in almonds; sprinkle crumb mixture over fruit filling.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening well.
Add sugar; beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts with spatula.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool before frosting with cream frosting.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Rinse and drain peppers under cold running water.
Remove seeds and menbranes; chop into very small pieces.
Beat eggs in a large bowl; blend in milk.
Stir in corn muffin mix, cheese, corn, onions, oil, baking powder and sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in pepper.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: pasta and vegetable salad
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size pieces.
Add pasta.
Pour Italian dressing over vegetables and chill overnight.

title: party ice cubes
directions: Mix together lemon juice, cherry liquid, sugar and cold water, stirring until sugar is completely dissolved.
Place 1 maraschino cherry and 1 mint leaf in each ice cube section.
Pour lemon mixture on top carefully. Freeze.
Use ice cubes in iced tea, lemonade or fruit punch.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Roll in balls and chill for several hours.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate.
Place on wax paper.
Chill 10 to 15 minutes.

title: reuben sandwich
directions: Butter each side of bread.
Place in a hot skillet, butter side down.
Put sauerkraut, then corned beef.
Place Swiss cheese and top with last piece of bread.
Let cook on one side approximately 3 minutes, turn (flip) to other side.
Cook another approximately 3 minutes.
Take out of skillet.
Turn skillet off.
Slice sandwich and enjoy.
Makes 1 serving.

title: mexican rotel chicken
directions: Stew and bone chicken.
Cut into small pieces.
Reserve stock. Grease a large casserole dish.
Dip Doritos into stock.
Layer Doritos into bottom of dish.
Next, add a layer of chicken, onion and green pepper.
Cover with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with chili powder and garlic powder.
Add 1/2 can of each soup.
Make a second layer as the first.
Pour Ro-Tel over all.
Top with more grated cheese.
Add paprika for color.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa and blend.
Then add sugar, water and salt; let blend.
Add vanilla and blend; let boil for about 1 minute, then pour into a butter-greased dish.

title: bacon wrap ups
directions: Cut slices of bacon into fourths.
Wrap each piece around an olive, pineapple chunk or water chestnut.
Secure with toothpick. Place under broiler 6 to 8 minutes on each side until bacon is done.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Blend milk and egg.
Add dry ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls into deep fryer. Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if you want.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp; add mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients and add onions.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream slaw
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients well. Pour over cabbage and onions. Blend well and chill.

title: aunt edie's chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Cool Whip, pudding and milk. Put a layer of crackers on bottom of pan (not crushed).
Add 1/2 of pudding mix, another layer of crackers and then the remaining pudding and then crackers again.
Spread topping over it all. Chill a day.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In a large (6-quart) Dutch oven, brown stew meat in butter until very brown and flavorful.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add chopped celery; stir and brown together with meat.
Add tomatoes; also add onion and garlic powder to taste.
Cover pot; simmer gently for about 2 hours.
(Check occasionally to make sure it doesn't cook dry.
You may need to add small amounts of water.) When meat is very tender, add 6 to 8 cups water and chopped vegetables.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Mix together Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut.
Pour over hot cake which has holes punched in top using a wooden spoon handle.
Cool cake and then top with 1 medium size Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with frozen coconut.
Refrigerate overnight for moistness.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together eggs, butter and sugar.
Mix together flour, soda and salt; add to first mixture.
Stir in bananas and vanilla. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 300° for 1 hour.
Just before bread is done, mix lemon juice, powdered sugar and cornstarch in pan on stove.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Spread on top of hot bread and let cool.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes. Add other ingredients. Cook slowly on stove until sweet potatoes are soft.

title: picante sauce
directions: Core and peel tomatoes; cut in small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
If you want sauce hotter, add more jalapeno peppers.

title: dressing for spinach salad
directions: Blend the ingredients (a blender works well).
Break 1 package of spinach into bite size pieces.
Drain 1 can of bean sprouts. Dice and fry some bacon.

title: little italy potato topper
directions: In a small bowl, combine yogurt, tomato, cheese, basil, oregano and salt. Cover and chill until ready to serve. To serve, spoon onto baked potato halves.

title: calico bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate over night.
Stir well before serving.
To add color, use chopped red and yellow bell peppers.

title: bakeless fruit cake
directions: Cut into in small pieces.
Crush vanilla wafers.
Add milk and mix well.
Pack very tightly in loaf type pan, and let stand at least 12 hours.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: squash patties
directions: Boil or steam squash.
Mash squash and add all ingredients. Make patties.
Fry or bake.

title: easy southwest chicken
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides. Remove; set aside. Spoon off fat. In same skillet, combine corn, soup, tomatoes, chili powder and garlic powder. Heat to boiling. Return chicken to skillet. Reduce heat to low. Cover; cook 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring occasionally. Serve over rice.

title: mini morsel tea biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl. With pastry blender or two knives, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in chocolate chips. Beat 3 eggs, evaporated milk and vanilla in medium bowl. Add to flour mixture all at once; stir with fork to form a soft dough. Turn dough onto well-floured surface. Knead 6 to 8 times. Pat dough to 3/4 inch thickness. Cut with floured 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter. Transfer to lightly greased baking sheets. Beat remaining egg and milk in small bowl; brush over biscuits. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 14 to 16 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire racks; serve warm. Makes 1 1/2 doz. biscuits.

title: cane creek apple pie
directions: Heat
oven
Put sliced apples in saucepan and add sugars
and orange juice.
Add just enough water to cover apple slices
and cook until tender.
Remove apple slices and boil syrup until it thickens slightly.
Fit pastry in a 9-inch pan and brush with egg white.
Add apple slices, syrup, nutmeg and
cinnamon and
dot
with
butter.
Strip top with pastry; brush
strips with egg white and sprinkle lightly with sugar. Bake 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bead
directions: In medium size bowl, mix together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Put the walnut meats into a blender.
Blend for 7 to 10 seconds.
Add to the dry ingredients.
Put the sugar, butter, egg, bananas and milk into blender.
Blend for 11 to 15 seconds.
(Stop blender to push bananas down if necessary.)
Pour over dry ingredients and mix until ingredients are well moistened. Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight and drain in a.m.
Pour beans in saucepan.
Add ham bone and water.
Cook slowly until beans are soft.
Add vegetables and cook until done.
Put through sieve. Season to taste and add minced parsley.
Serve very hot with bread fingers.

title: ombly's muffins
directions: Stir together buttermilk and soda; beat egg and add buttermilk mixture and oil.
Sift together flour, sugar and salt and add to mixture; mix well.
Add cereals, raisins and apples.
Pour into muffin tins; bake 15 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.
Makes about 24 muffins.

title: cherry delight
directions: Crush graham crackers and spread in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt margarine and pour over graham cracker crumbs; pack down with a fork.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix sugar, salad oil, pepper, vinegar and salt. Pour over beans, green pepper and onion.
Chill 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: spicy cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form tiny cocktail size meatballs.
Cook in a medium frying pan with a small amount of oil so meatballs don't stick.

title: cheesy vegetable "un-quiche"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In pan, cook onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
In medium bowl, toss cheese with flour; add egg and milk mixing well.
Add broccoli, onion and carrot. Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes, or until set and golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting and serving.
Serves 6.

title: greek sauce baked pork chops and potatoes
directions: Arrange chops and potatoes in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with spices, salt and pepper.
Add tomato sauce.
Pour water over all. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
You can cover if it starts to brown too quick.

title: fruit ice ring punch
directions: Place frozen juices and water into large bowl.
Stir until frozen juices are thawed.
Pour mixture into punch bowl over ice cubes.
Gently pour ginger ale and soda water that has been chilled.
Add iced Fruit Ring. Garnish with sliced fruit and mint.

title: black walnut fruit cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and jam.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in nuts, raisins and coconut.
Pour into 9-inch tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tropical ham dinner
directions: Amounts of ingredients depend upon how many you intend to serve.
This recipe can be stretched or reduced to accomodate the size of your dinner party.
For 4 to 6, I use a 9 x 13-inch pan, layering several slices of canned ham in the center.
On the edges, place the canned yams.
On top of the ham, put canned peach halves and on the yams, place quartered bananas.
Over all of this, put a generous sprinkling of brown sugar.
Pour over all this, the vinegar and wine.
Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut; return to oven and cook until coconut is light brown.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix well.
Add a little mayonnaise or cream.
Add pepper to taste.

title: broccoli cheddar cheese quiche
directions: Put pie crust into a quiche pan and crimp edges.
Prick bottom with fork.
Bake 5 minutes to set crust.
In a skillet, saute onion until brown.
Sprinkle cheese over bottom of pie crust, then add onion.
Place broccoli and zucchini on top of that.
In a medium bowl, combine milk, eggs, salt, nutmeg, red pepper and black pepper.
Stir until smooth.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
In separate bowl mix sugar and eggs.
Add chocolate mixture to sugar and eggs.
Add flour and vanilla and mix well.
Pour in greased pie pan and bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve hot with scoop of ice cream. Great!

title: bean fondue dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have ready a 1 1/2-quart ovenproof casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients, except 1 cup of the cheese, until well blended.
Spread in baking dish and sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: clown make-up
directions: Using a rubber spatula, blend the first three ingredients on a white plate until a smooth paste is formed.
Add 3 to 4 drops of glycerin for a creamier consistency.
Yield should be enough to complete a child's face.
When applying the make-up to the face, you will have better results if you stroke in one direction.
For easy removal, use shortening, cold cream or baby oil.

title: cheese grits
directions: Add all ingredients to grits.
Bake in square pan at 300° for 45 minutes.
May be topped with Cheddar cheese and baked 15 minutes longer.

title: ham toss salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Combine all ingredients.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fried bows
directions: Beat eggs.
Starting with four cups of flour, make well on a large baking
board.
Pour	eggs into center well and all other ingredients, mixing
with
a
fork.
Begin	blending
in flour from the walls of the well.
Knead dough into two balls. Roll out one ball at a time into a round circle.
Roll as thin as possible. Cut
into long strips and then into smaller ones (approximately 4 inches).
Strips
of
dough may also be knotted.
Heat 1/2	gallon oil
(Crisco or other preferred frying oil).
Fry strips
or bows until golden brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when your ready to serve.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Add salt to cucumbers and onions and let stand.
Rinse in cold water.
Drain; put in kettle.
Add remaining ingredients and enough water to boil mixture for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: dinner salad
directions: Cook rice and water until done, about 20 minutes.
Do not drain.
Add gelatin, sugar and pineapple to the cooked rice.
Mix well and let cool and then add Cool Whip.

title: classic philly cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325° (300° if using dark nonstick spring form pan). Combine crumbs, 3 Tbsp. butter; press firmly onto bottom of 9 inch spring form pan. Bake for 10 minutes. Mix cream cheese, 1 c. sugar, flour and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add sour cream; mix well. Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended. Pour over crust. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until center is almost set. Loosen cake from side of pan; cool before removing rim of pan. Refrigerate 4
hours or overnight.

title: ham pie
directions: In medium size bowl, beat eggs well.
Stir in ham, cheese, corn, evaporated milk, onion, salt, thyme and parsley flakes. Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place triangles in ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Cover with foil and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
For easier serving, let stand 5 minutes before cutting into wedges.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Clean potatoes and rub skins with vegetable oil and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Allow potato to cool to touch. Cut in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4 to 1/8-inch shell.
Deep fry in hot oil (375°) for 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towel.
Place skins on baking sheet, sprinkle with seasoned salt, cheese and bacon crumbs. Place under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve with sour cream.

title: cheese soup
directions: In large cooker, saute celery, onion and carrots in margarine. Add Cheez Whiz and stir until melted.
Put cornstarch in Cheez Whiz jar and add milk to fill jar, then shake.
Pour in cooker with other ingredients and add chicken broth.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Serve nice and hot.

title: lace cookies
directions: Melt butter; set aside to cool.
Mix all other ingredients together and add cooled butter and mix.
Place foil, shiny side up on cookie sheet.
Drop cookie mix 1/2 teaspoon at a time 2 inches apart (very important).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven or until golden brown (very delicate).
Bet you can't eat just one!

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce as listed.
Mix well.
Add to the following: cauliflower, broccoli and green onion.

title: old fashion bread pudding
directions: Mix liquid ingredients and pour over bread cubes in a large bowl or pan.
Place pan or bowl in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, knife comes out clean.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine boiling water, oats and margarine
in
a mixing bowl. Cover
and
let
stand 20 minutes.
Add
sugar,
eggs, flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: one egg cake
directions: Mix together about 4 to 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (in a greased pan).
Split in half and put applesauce inside.
(You may bake in an iron skillet.)
This recipe can be made and baked in about 35 minutes.

title: hot applesauce bread
directions: Heat applesauce and add soda.
Cut butter up slightly and add to applesauce.
Stir to melt butter, then add all the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° until done.

title: frozen peaches
directions: Mix orange juice and sugar.
Let stand while preparing peaches.
Combine peaches and mixture.
Fill containers and freeze.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Combine raisins in water and simmer for 15 minutes.
Let cool. Add beaten egg.
Add shortening, rolled oats, sugar substitute and vanilla.
Add sifted flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix all together well.
Pour into greased 1-layer cake pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Use peaches, not too ripe.
Peel them and stick each one with 4 or 5 cloves.
Simmer sugar, vinegar and cinnamon together for 20 minutes.
Put peaches in syrup a few at a time and cook until tender.
Skim out and pack in sterilized jars.
Boil down syrup until thick.
Fill the jars with it and seal.

title: banana cake
directions: Mash bananas in mixing bowl.
Add the other ingredients in the order listed, beating well after each addition.
Pour into greased sheet cake pan.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
Dust with seasoned flour.
Brown meat in butter.
Add onion, mushrooms and garlic.
Brown lightly. Stir in broth.
Cover and cook for 1 hour or until tender. Gradually add sour cream.
Boil noodles.
Serve beef mixture over noodles.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cauliflower and broccoli toss
directions: Blend mayonnaise, dressing mix, sugar and vinegar in bowl until smooth.
Combine green onions, cauliflower and broccoli in salad bowl.
Mix lightly.
Add dressing; mix well.
Chill, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
May add bacon bits before serving.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: Mix and make loaf.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: molasses pie
directions: Melt molasses and sugar; then add milk, butter, flour, and eggs.

title: brownies
directions: Combine chocolate and butter; set aside. Beat eggs and sugar together; add melted chocolate/butter mixture. Add flour and baking powder. Add vanilla and nuts; stir after each addition. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in an 8 x 8 pan.

title: huzarensla
directions: Cut all eggs in half.
Separate the yolks from the whites.
Cut the whites from the eggs in small pieces and mix with vegetables. Mash egg yolks with a fork in a bowl and add mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar to taste.
Add dressing to vegetables and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Use within two hours.
Do not make ahead of time!

title: sweetheart salad(serves 12)
directions: Heat pineapple with sugar.
Add gelatin which has been softened in 1/4 cup water, stirring until melted.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo's until fine in a bowl.
Pour 1/2 of Oreo's into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese well; mix the 2 packages of pudding mix, powdered sugar, vanilla and milk into cream cheese until well mixed and thick.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Pour into pan over Oreo crumbs.
Put other half of crumbs on top.
Refrigerate several hours to overnight before serving.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add beans; cover and cook 3 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Cut bacon in half lengthwise; place on microwave plate.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until edges are curling.
Place 4-5 beans on each strip; wrap bacon around beans and tie in a knot.
Place on 8-inch baking dish.
Drizzle with dressing.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Broil until bacon is crisp.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour in one deep 9-inch unbaked crust or 2 shallow 9-inch crusts.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Place layer of bananas on graham cracker crust.
Combine condensed milk with lemon juice; mix.
Top bananas with condensed milk mixture, then add layer of crushed pineapple which has been drained.
Combine whipping cream with sugar.
Add this over crushed pineapple.
Repeat layers.
Garnish with coconut, nuts and chopped cherries.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.

title: cucumbers and onions
directions: Slice cucumbers thin; place in large bowl.
Add onions and green pepper.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over the cucumber mix.
Do not stir.
Place in fridge for 24 hours.
Remove from fridge and stir well.
Serve cold.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, carrots, pineapple and vanilla.
Mix until moistened. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer.
Bake in greased and lightly floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan in 350° oven for about 35 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Place brisket fat side up in roasting pan.
Roast, uncovered, without liquid at 350° for 2 hours.
Combine catsup, brown sugar, water, onion, liquid smoke, Tabasco sauce, chili powder and salt in blender container; process until smooth.
Pour over brisket. Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Roast, covered, for 3 to 4 hours or until done to taste, basting every 30 minutes.
Slice very thin.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: hungarian slaw
directions: Boil ingredients together 1 minute.
Pour boiling water over cabbage and onions; cover.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Stir cabbage and onion together before the oil mixture is poured over.
Do not stir again until you are ready to serve.
Will keep up to 6 weeks.

title: chocolate surprises
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Mix in remaining ingredients, except marshmallows.
Drop batter from teaspoon onto lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Press half a marshmallow, cut side down, into center of each cookie.
Return to oven for 2 minutes. Do not leave in longer than 2 minutes!

title: shrimp and crawfish pasta
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in a large pot.
Saute until onion is clear.
Add the next 4 ingredients to the pot and cook until thickened.
Add shrimp and crawfish.
Add pasta.
Makes 15 - 20 servings.

title: italian biscuits(the original!  handed down three generations)
directions: Butter cookie sheet.
Cream first 3 ingredients.
Stir in flour.
Add almonds.
Roll dough into long thin strips, approximately 2 inches wide.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool, then slice strips into smaller strips.

title: maple spice cake
directions: Put it
all
together
in the mixer bowl and beat for 3 minutes.
It's
so simple and simply delicious.
This electric mixer cake
is
put together in order of ingredients.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: brown sugar pie(easy to make; melts in your mouth)
directions: Beat all ingredients together in a large bowl of electric mixer.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until set.
If desired, top with whipped cream.
Will make 2 pies if frozen pie crusts are used.
Freezes well after baking.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Sift flour together with soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream the butter or shortening thoroughly.
Add sugar and continue beating by hand or mixer.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, and vanilla and lemon extract.
To the creamed mixture (by hand), add the flour alternately with the cup of buttermilk.
Bake in a tube pan, 9-inch diameter tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mama best ever brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs and nuts in.
Mix flour and cocoa together; add to butter and sugar mixture.
Bake in greased shallow pan at 350° for about 15 to 25 minutes.
Yields 12 to 16.

title: midnight magic cake
directions: Sift together flour, tartar or baking powder, salt, cocoa, soda and sugar.
Add shortening, vanilla, milk and food coloring. Beat 2 minutes with electric beaten.
Add eggs; beat additional 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Simmer chicken livers with poultry seasoning in enough water to make 2 cups of broth.
When livers are tender, chop fine or grind (reserve broth).
In deep skillet, brown beef in cooking oil.
Add onion, bell pepper, celery, salt, pepper and Tabasco. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth.
Simmer for 30 minutes before adding chopped livers.
Combine cooked rice to meat.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: break away bread
directions: Dissolve Crisco in 1 cup boiling water.
Allow to cool.
In bowl, dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Add Crisco/water.
Add flour; mix.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix together and serve with ginger snaps or apple slices.

title: luscious lemon pie
directions: Combine the sugar, cornstarch, oleo, lemon rind (grated), unbeaten egg yolks and milk in double boiler or cook in microwave container until thick.
Stir at intervals while cooking.
Fold sour cream in cooked ingredients and pour in baked pie shell (9-inch).
Chill for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.
Keeps well.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Blend; pour into a greased pie dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
If needed, bake 10 minutes longer.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix English peas, celery, almonds, pickles, cheese, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and onion.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add parsley, salt and pepper to taste. Pour mix into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in baking dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve both packages of jello in the boiling water.
Add pineapple with its juice, cranberry sauce and nuts.
Stir until well blended.
Fold in sour cream and chill until firm.

title: one pan cranberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously grease bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Stir oil, milk, sour cream, eggs, baking mix, sugar and orange peel in pan with a fork until moistened.
Beat vigorously 1 minute.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Bake until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run a knife or metal spatula around sides of loaf to loosen.
Remove from pan.
If desired, cool loaf completely and drizzle with Orange Glaze.

title: "pioneer biscuit mix dumplings"
directions: Combine in order given.
Drop by spoonful into boiling chicken or beef broth.
Cover lightly and simmer without removing cover for 5 minutes. Serve hot.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Makes 14 ounces of sweetened condensed milk and costs about 25 cents to make compared to $1.89 a can. Use this in any recipe that calls for sweetened condensed milk.

title: bacon cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, add egg, milk and bacon (cut in small pieces).
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes in oiled pan.
Put strips of bacon on top before baking, if desired.

title: picnic salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing with mayonnaise.
Chill until ready to serve.
If desired, serve on lettuce.
Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine bananas, egg, milk, molasses and oil until well blended. In separate bowl, combine flour, bran, soda and salt. Stir flour mixture into banana mixture until just moistened. Do not over mix. Fold in raisins. Spoon batter into well greased muffin pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mother's pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl until well blended.
Bake for 35 minutes for 5 to 6 small loaf pans or 1 hour for large loaf pan at 350°.
Cool well before slicing.
Better if it sits for a day.
Freezes well.

title: risotto
directions: Saute 5 chopped onions and celery in margarine until golden. Add rice and chicken broth and cook, stirring occasionally until rice is done (30 minutes - white rice; 45 minutes brown rice).
In separate pan, saute 4 chopped onions, chicken livers and mushrooms.
Add salt, pepper, basil and sage.
Place rice on a large serving dish.
Make a large impression in the middle and fill with liver and mushroom mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Flatten chicken breast with hand.
Dip chicken in egg then in crumbs to coat.
In skillet over medium heat, melt margarine, add chicken and brown on both sides.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Cover for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Yields 4 servings.

title: orange raisin loaf
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly butter a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Heat orange juice until almost boiling.
Put raisins, butter and orange rind in a bowl, then pour orange juice over them.
Set aside to cool.
In another bowl, beat eggs with sugar until thick.
Add vanilla and stir into raisin mixture.
Add sifted dry ingredients to raisin mixture and stir until moistened.
Fold in walnuts.
Lightly spread batter into pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Remove the loaf to a wire rack.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: cheese spoon bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a saucepan; add 1 cup milk.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Reserve 1/3 of the cheese for top.
Cut remaining cheese into cubes.
Add to the cooked mixture and stir until cheese melts.
Add remaining milk and the eggs and mix well.
Pour into a greased shallow baking dish.
Top with reserved cheese. Bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: easy french onion soup
directions: In a 5-quart pot, saute sliced onions in olive oil.
When onions start to get soft, add bouillon cubes, consomme, water, salt and pepper.
Bring soup to a boil for about 3 minutes, then turn on medium-low and cover.
Cook for about 20 minutes, then eat and enjoy.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter and add brown sugar; let cool.
Add egg and mix. Mix flour, baking powder and salt (may omit).
Add to first mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stew beef
directions: Roll beef in salt, pepper and flour.
Brown beef over medium heat in small amount of cooking oil.
Add beef, soup and water. Cook in crock-pot until tender, about 6 hours.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Peel, seed and cut up pumpkin.
Cook with small amount of boiling, salted water until very tender.
Drain and mash.
Whip the pulp with mixer until smooth.
Measure 6 cups of pumpkin.
In a large kettle, combine pumpkin, brown sugar, grated lemon rind, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Cook and stir until thick, stirring constantly to
prevent scorching.
Spoon into hot, sterilized half-pint jars and seal.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 8 half pints.

title: great blue cheese dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients. Refrigerate several hours. Shake well before serving. Keeps for months.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° until done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In large bowl cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well with electric mixer.
Stir in bananas and lemon juice. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture and stir only until blended.
Add nuts and fold into mixture.

title: double chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add vanilla, water and egg to first mixture, mixing well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Yields 60 cookies. These freeze well. Dough may be chilled.

title: sopa - fiesta
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: never fail meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into loaf.
Place in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: onion burger
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Make into patties and fry.

title: cinnamon rolls(approximately 20 rolls)
directions: Drain cheese.
Cut 1 cup, plus 1 tablespoon of butter into flakes.
Add cheese, salt, vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Knead on floured surface.
Wrap in aluminum foil and chill 1 hour.
Roll out to 16 x 24-inch rectangle.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter; brush on dough.
Wash the raisins in hot water.
Mix ground nuts, cinnamon and sugar.
Spread mix on dough, then add raisins.
Roll up dough, starting with small end.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry.
Heat margarine and chocolate in small saucepan over low heat until melted.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt and syrup with hand beater.
Stir in chocolate mixture and pecans.
Pour into pastry lined pie plate.
Bake until set, 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm or refrigerate. After serving, refrigerate any remaining pie immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Contains 630 calories per serving.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook all ingredients at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, stirring once.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with sauteed fresh garlic and onion.
Drain fat.
Saute sausage; drain fat.
Add with ground beef mixture in large stock pot.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and sauce.
Stir together.
Add parsley, basil, oregano, salt and pepper to season as desired.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours and add hot water as needed to create sauce thickness desired.

title: buttermilk corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs with buttermilk; add this to dry ingredients.
Stir in shortening.
Pour batter into hot, greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix in 6 to 8-quart container the Hershey bars (broken in pieces), dainties, vanilla, Marshmallow Creme and butter.
Mix sugar and milk in 4 to 6-quart saucepan.
Let milk come to boil. Cook for 6 minutes.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Blend until smooth and creamy.
Fold in pecans.
Drop balls of the mixture onto wax paper with a tablespoon.
Let stand 4 to 6 hours or until completely chilled before removing from wax paper.
Makes 6 pounds of the best fudge ever.

title: stir-fry in one dish
directions: Cook rice per package instructions.
Cut steak into thin strips (across the grain), and cut both kinds of squash into 1/4-inch rounds.
Cut onions into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Stir-fry steak in oil.
Add all vegetables (and garlic if desired) and stir-fry until almost done.
Cover and cook for a few minutes. Add cooked rice and reheat for a few more minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with soy sauce on side.

title: easy chicken dinner
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients.
Add 3/4 cup water; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut onion and pepper in round slices and put in dish with carrots.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over carrots, pepper and onion.
Cover and place in refrigerator at least 12 hours.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: browned pecan candy
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients together until they start to brown. Add other ingredients (except vanilla).
Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, add vanilla.
Cool 5 minutes.
Beat until white.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: reese's brownie cups
directions: Prepare brownie mix as written on box.
Place 2-inch foiled cupcake papers on cookie sheet.
Fill each cupcake paper 3/4 full. Bake 10 to 12 minutes (degrees on box).
Remove from oven and place Reese's candy in center of each cupcake.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes approximately 30 to 33 bite-sized treats.

title: springtide salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar; cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Chill thoroughly.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Spread oil in the bottom of an 11 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer each of the ingredients in the order listed, seasoning the raw potatoes with salt and combining the tomato soup with the 1/2 cup water before pouring into the casserole.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: salmon patties(diabetic)
directions: Remove bones and break up salmon with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and combine thoroughly.
Make into patties and bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes six patties.
One serving = 2 lean meat, 1 bread and 2 fat.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Brown onions and celery in butter in a heavy skillet.
Combine bread crumbs and seasonings.
Pour in chicken broth.
Stir lightly to blend.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes.

title: jiffy rolls
directions: Mix cake mix and yeast.
Dissolve salt in water; stir into cake mix.
Add enough flour to make smooth dough.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Punch down and make into 12 rolls.
Brush with butter and let rise 2 more hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(I use a muffin pan.)

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients except garlic powder and black pepper.
Add garlic powder and black pepper to taste.
Simmer for at least 1 hour to blend flavors.

title: baked apple slices with topping
directions: Arrange sliced apples in ovenproof baking dish.
Pour over them a mixture of marmalade, orange juice and nutmeg.
Mix together in a small bowl the cornflakes and brown sugar.
Cut in butter.
Sprinkle topping over apples. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done. After baking, wait until cool and then top with a dollop of whipped topping or whipped cream.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix thawed hash browns and melted, room temperature butter. Then add cream of mushroom soup. Add onion powder and salt. Add sour cream and 3 cups grated cheese. Spread in 9 x 13 glass dish. Top with 1 cup grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients
and spread in bottom of round baking dish.
Pour cocktail sauce over cream cheese mixture.

title: cliff's peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water together and cook to 240°, stirring constantly.
Add the peanuts and cook to 280°, stirring constantly.
Add margarine, cut in pieces.
Cook to 294°.
Mix baking soda and salt and add to candy.
Turn off fire.
Stir constantly until it rises second time or takes on the peanut brittle color.
Pour on two Teflon cookie sheets.
Candy will spread itself.
Keep stirring as you pour.

title: rigatoni a la vodka
directions: Combine heavy cream with melted butter in a large pan. Add tomatoes and tomato paste; simmer at very low heat. Add vodka to sauce just before taking mixture off stove.
Pour sauce over rigatoni. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese as you mix the sauce and pasta. Pour into serving dish and sprinkle additional Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: cheese pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°, 375° and 325°.
Baking Time: 15 minutes each temperature.

title: potato cheese hurry-up
directions: Mix all together, then add two 1 pound cans of sliced white potatoes (drained).
Mix thoroughly.
Cook until heated, about 30 minutes at 425°.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Wash chicken. Cut into large chunks size pieces.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix until mixture forms soft dough, then have grease ready hot.
Drop in.
It just takes a minute to cook.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender (may bake).
Let cool, peel and cut into 3/4-inch thick slices.
Arrange potatoes in a lightly greased shallow 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine sugar, pecans, juices and cinnamon, mixing well; pour over potatoes, tossing gently.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, spooning glaze over potatoes occasionally.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, combine the water, cabbage, bacon, carrots and dry potato mix with sauce.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Combine the milk and cornstarch.
Add to soup along with frozen beans.
Simmer, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes more until beans are tender.
Makes 4 to 6 main dish servings.

title: chocolate star cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into balls, then roll in sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Press in stars and bake 2 to 4 more minutes.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Wash the beans.
Place in a large pot and cold water to cover. Let soak overnight.
Or, boil the beans in 6 to 8 cups of water with a dash of baking soda for 2 minutes, then set aside for 1 hour.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix salt and vegetables together.
Let stand in ice water 3 hours and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a rolling boil.
Seal in canning jars.

title: lorene's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and put in a glass casserole dish.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausages and let cool.
Place cubed bread in bottom of greased 3-quart oblong Pyrex dish or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Slice sausages into bite size pieces and put on top of bread.
Slice water chestnuts and add to top of sausages.
Top this with grated cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Cook in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and place onions on top. Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: banana grape salad
directions: Cut the grapes to make 2 cups and add the sugar.
Set aside. Stir once in awhile. When ready to serve, slice the bananas in about 4 or more until it looks like equal amounts of both fruit or use your own judgment. Depends on the size of family.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and juice.
Cook until begins to get clear. Stir in apples and spices.
Pour into crust and cover with crust. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter or margarine and 2 eggs together (will be thick).
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, 1 box powdered sugar and vanilla together (will be thin). Pour on top of other mixture and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini and onion for 5 minutes; drain water.
Mix soup, sour cream, zucchini, carrots and onions and set aside.
Mix Stove Top (dry) and add seasoning with melted butter.
Put 1/2 of crumbs in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour zucchini mixture over crumbs. Top with rest of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese the last 5 minutes of baking.
(Turkey or chicken could be added.)
Use 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: fish roll-ups
directions: Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Heat oven to 350°.
Brush fish with soy sauce on one side.
Divide shrimp among fish fillets.
Roll up the fish. Brush tops with soy sauce.
Bake for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: cookie pie
directions: Mix
first
4 ingredients, then add chocolate chips and nuts. Bake
at
350° for 20 minutes in 2 (9-inch) pie plates. Do not bake over 20 minutes.

title: orange zucchini cake
directions: Mix well all the ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Line pan with enough cookies for a crust.
Stir the rest of the cookies in with softened ice cream and Cool Whip.
Pour into pan and freeze.
Garnish with nuts and chocolate sauce.

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage
directions: Soak rice in cold water for 1/2 hour.
Remove outer leaves of cabbage.
Cut off hard parts, then parboil for 5 minutes. (Optional) Chop onion and fry lightly; drain.
Drain rice; beat egg and mix with meat.
Season and place meat mixture in leaves.
Roll up securely.
Cover with hot water.
Add tomato sauce and cook 1 1/2 hours, then melt fat and blend with flour.
Add 1/2 to 1 teaspoon paprika; dissolve in water and pour over cabbage.
Boil 1/2 hour longer.

title: roux
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add flour in small amounts while stirring.
Continue to stir until roux turns light brown.
Lower heat.
Continue to cook until roux looks like dark chocolate.
Be careful not to burn.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions and salt with cold water and ice cubes.
Let set 2 hours.
Mix sugar, vinegar, turmeric and celery seed and cook until boiling.
Pack cucumbers and onions in jars. Cover with hot liquid.
Process in canner about 15 minutes.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Mix together.
Pour into molds and freeze.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix cream, sugar, flavoring and condensed milk.
Fill the ice cream container with regular milk.
Cover and turn your churn on and start with a little ice and then a little salt; continue until up to top of churn.
Keep adding as it melts, plus salt until ice cream gets hard, around 20 minutes.

title: cornpone
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Add milk until you can work batter. Add eggs and beat until mixed well.
Add enough milk to make thin so they can be fried like pancakes on griddle.
Serve warm with butter.

title: luscious strawberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries immediately and mix gently. Chill until slightly congealed.
Add pineapple and nuts and mix. Put 1/2 of gelatin mixture into mold.
Chill slightly.
Fold sour cream into remaining gelatin mixture and pour over mixture in mold.
Chill until firm.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Beat well with electric mixer until smooth.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes at 375° for 1 hour.
Split lengthwise. Scoop insides into mixing bowl and reserve 6 empty shells.
Puree potatoes. Add remainder of ingredients except Parmesan cheese and paprika. Fill shells and sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
May omit egg yolks and use no-fat sour cream for lighter version.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Mix walnuts and margarine in a 9-inch plate until well blended.
Press onto the bottom and up the sides of pie plate. Refrigerate.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix pistachio pudding and chopped orange with softened Cool Whip and chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Can be served with wheat crackers, or on your choice on bread, cut into your choice of shapes.

title: lilikoi jelly
directions: Boil water and	sugar for 1 minute.
Remove from stove. Add lilikoi juice,
lemon
juice and pectin.
Pack in hot jars immediately.

title: chewy peanut picnic bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, peanuts and raisins.
Spread evenly into ungreased 12 x 7-inch baking dish. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely; cut into bars.

title: vegetarian pecan casserole
directions: Mix eggs
with	cottage
cheese.
Stir	in pecans, sour cream, oil, broth, cheese and onion.
Add Special K cereal and mix lightly.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Mix the Veg-All, soup and chicken; place in pie crust in a 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Place top crust on pie.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; set aside to cool.
Cut up tomatoes, lettuce and onion.
Put into large bowl; add olives.
Shred cheese.
Mix contents together.
Add cheese.
Smash Doritos chips into small pieces and add to rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Top with sour cream and favorite taco sauce.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine until soft, then blend in sugar.
Add vanilla, salt and flour.
Mix well and add chopped pecans.
Roll dough into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: hard rock candy
directions: Cook ingredients quickly without stirring to 290°.
Add flavor extract and desired food coloring.
Pour quickly into greased square pan.
Crack into desired pieces.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and dip by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Cross with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 13 minutes.

title: *lentil soup 2
directions: Wash lentils, rinse and drain in cold water.
In saucepan, saute celery, carrots, parsley, onion and garlic in oil over low heat for 15 minutes (in saucepan).
Add tomato sauce and bay leaf. Boil water and add lentils, vegetables, George Washington seasoning, oregano, bay leaf, vinegar, Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Yields 10 servings. (Freezes well.)

title: fudge bars
directions: Mix all together in one bowl, but mix very well.
Pour into greased, long cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Bake approximately 30 minutes or until tests done by using toothpick at 350°.

title: pecan-beer shrimp with sauces
directions: Devein and butterfly shrimp by splitting almost, but not quite through, with a paring knife.
Set aside.
Heat 3-inches oil in heavy skillet to 350°.
Mix vanilla wafer crumbs and pecans. Set aside.
Beat eggs in a medium bowl; stir in flour and beer.
Mix well.
Dip shrimp into beer batter and roll in crumb mixture.
Fry in hot oil for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot with sauces.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in melted butter then in crumb mixture. Arrange chicken so they do not overlap in shallow roasting pan. Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal and salt.
Add boiling hot water, enough to mix well.
Make into small cakes and cook in hot oil until brown.

title: pennsylvania dutch light ginger cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Blend on lowest speed or by hand.
If cookies dough is too dry to handle easily, work in milk or cream, a tsp. at a time.
Chill. Roll out to 1/8 inch on lightly floured board.
Cut into shapes. Bake on ungreased baking sheet 6 to 8 minutes.
While still warm; brush thin icing (the consistency of pancake batter) on cookies with a pastry brush.
This will harden and appear transparent. Decorate if desired.

title: green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, blend soup, milk, shoyu and a dash of pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions and bake additional 5 minutes.

title: french strawberry pie
directions: Wash berries, hull and drain well.
Reserve half the berries for filling and half for glaze.
Use the poorest for the glaze. Mash and strain berries for glaze until juice is extracted (roughly 3/4 cup juice).
Bring juice to boiling point in small saucepan.
Stir in a little cold water to cornstarch to make it a little liquidy.
Slowly add cornstarch mixture and sugar to the juice, stirring while adding.
Cook slowly 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, sugar, oleo and salt and cool to lukewarm.
Add half the flour and mix well.
Add yeast and beaten egg; beat well.
Stir in remaining flour.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise to double its size (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Roll to a 18 x 10-inch rectangle 1/2-inch thick.
Spread with 1/4 cup butter. Combine 1/4 cup sugar with cinnamon.
Sprinkle over dough.
Roll and cut in 1-inch pieces.
Allow to double.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375° in a large muffin pan.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into Pet pie crust.
Double ingredients for 2 pies.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: beanless chili-cheese dip(microwave)
directions: Dice cheese.
Place cheese, chili and chilies into microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Microwave for 3 minutes more.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: esther's oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add brown and white sugar and margarine.
Stir until margarine melts. Add eggs and mix well. Sift flour, cocoa, salt and soda.
Add to mixture plus 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle rest of chocolate chips and the nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Good served with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry with towel.
Heat oil and butter in a Dutch oven.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time, and brown well on all sides.
Remove browned chicken and set aside.
Add onion and garlic to Dutch oven and saute until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Make sure tomatoes are well mashed.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together until fluffy.
Add salt, syrup, eggs and vanilla.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pie shell. Pour the filling over the pecans.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes longer.

title: pickled beans
directions: Cook beans until bullets are soft, but firm. Cool. Pack firmly into sterilized pint jars to within 1 inch of top. Fill with preceding mixture to cover top of beans. Using a knife, work salt mixture down sides of cans so all beans will be covered. Put caps on loosely; let ferment from 8 to 10 days or until fermentation stops. Clean lids; screw on tightly and process in a hot water bath for 30 minutes. Begin to count when water boils.

title: super easy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour Catalina dressing into a shallow bowl.
Pour bread crumbs into a shallow bowl.
Dip chicken in dressing, then roll in bread crumbs to coat.
Place on shallow baking sheet.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: miracle white bread
directions: This seems more complicated than it is.
Takes less than 2 hours to have fresh bread.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add cooked rice, mushroom soup, chicken soup, tomato paste, taco sauce and green chilies.
Heat through. Crush the Doritos chips.
Layer half the chips in a baking dish. Add meat mixture and top with remaining chips.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Heat in a 375° oven until the cheese melts.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon melted butter, cereal and paprika; set aside.
Stir together and make a white sauce of 2 tablespoons melted butter, flour, salt, pepper, onion, milk and sour cream. Mix together the beans, cheese and sauce.
Pour into baking dish. Top with cereal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: remi's chocolate cake
directions: In a small bowl, stir together cocoa and boiling water until smooth; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round pans (9 x 1 1/2-inch).
In a large mixer bowl, cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Blend in cocoa mixture.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.
Cool completely and frost with Chocolate Buttercream Frosting.

title: virginia box bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add eggs, sugar, salt, butter and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch the dough down.

title: date loaf
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a full foaming boil in a saucepan. Add dates.
Cook until dates mixture dissolves or until mixture reaches soft boil stage.
Remove from fire and add nuts.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour mixture onto a wet cloth and roll up.
Slice when cool.

title: hot dip
directions: In the bottom of baking dish, spread cream cheese and then spread chili on top of cream cheese and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cheese needs to be completely melted.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix together and chill 24 hours.
Serve with bread or crackers.

title: heartthrob cookies
directions: Beat sugar and shortening with electric mixer until fluffy. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Tint, chill and shape as directed.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done, but not browned.
Cool on wire rack.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Grease bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine first 6 ingredients (do not use a mixer).
Pour into pan.
Spread dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin.
Sprinkle with pecans and pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes; check at 55 minutes.

title: husband's delight
directions: 1st layer:
Mix flour, pecans and oleo; pack in bottom of "Pyrex" dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup and milk together.
Place in baking dish. Mix broth, butter and stuffing together.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon together. Blend beaten eggs and sugar; add pumpkin and oil, blending well. Add flour mixture and nuts.
Makes 1 large tube pan or 2 loaf cakes.
Bake large cake in 350° oven for about 1 hour or loaves for about 50 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix vanilla wafers and margarine and push into 9 x 12-inch cake pan.

title: cranberry fruit nut bread
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse oatmeal.
Combine orange juice, rind and egg.
Add to the dry ingredients and mix just to moisten.
Carefully fold in 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1 or 2 cups cranberries.
(If you use frozen cranberries, put them through the chopper in frozen state.)

title: pineapple and strawberries
directions: You will need cocktail picks.

title: *fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat sugar and egg together.
Add fruit cocktail and stir until blended.
Sift flour, soda and salt, blending into fruit mixture.
Pour into greased 10 x 14-inch sheet pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, mixed with the chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or ice cream. Serves 12 to 15.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except last 3.
Stir last 3 ingredients in and bake at 325° for 15 to 16 minutes.
Yield:
100 plus.

title: pear pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients to make a custard.
Then pour over pears.
Use your favorite pie crust recipe or an already prepared crust.
Bake in a 375°
oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken barbados
directions: Trim chicken and cut into 3/4-inch strips. Mix eggs and milk to make an egg wash. Dip chicken into flour to coat, then egg wash, then flour. Shake off excess flour. Heat butter over medium heat and brown chicken strips on all sides. Don't overcrowd or chicken will steam rather than brown. They will take 2 or 3 minutes on each side. Remove from pan and add honey and rum; mix well. Add chicken and cook for 10 minutes longer. (Add rum carefully. It's flammable and might flare up if careless.)

title: oven-roasted beets *
directions: Trim beets, leaving some stalk intact (so they won't bleed). Place in baking dish with a little water on the bottom or wrap in foil.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for about 50 minutes (a little longer for foil wrapped beets), until tender.
Pierce with fork to check tenderness.
When cool enough to handle, remove the skins; coat with butter and salt and pepper to taste.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Blend well.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Boil together until candy thermometer reads 236° or until temperature reaches the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts.
Continue stirring until no longer glossy.
Cool on baking sheet, then separate.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese and butter with mixer. Mix pudding and milk for 2 minutes with mixer. Add the 2 mixtures together in a large bowl. Fold in Cool Whip. Layer pudding mixture, then top with crushed cookies. Layer again with pudding mixture and end with cookies on top.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt and onion with 1/2 cup of vinegar.
Gradually add oil and remaining vinegar.
Then add celery seed.
Beat until mixture is well blended.

title: divinity
directions: Use stove on medium-high.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon; pour over apples and let stand 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Bake in a greased 9 x 5-inch pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let rest 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: easy lemon chicken
directions: Crush enough crackers to coat all breasts thoroughly.
Dampen breasts with water, then coat both sides with cracker crumbs. Sprinkle both sides generously with lemon pepper.
Bake in casserole dish covered for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes uncovered to brown chicken.
(No oil or butter needed in baking; nonstick spray optional.)

title: gingerbread
directions: Add beaten eggs to brown sugar, molasses and shortening.
Add flour, soda, spices, baking powder and boiling water; mix well. Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Put coconut in raw crust.
Blend sugar, flour, eggs, milk, vanilla and butter together.
Pour over coconut in raw crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza bites
directions: Divide each biscuit in half or thirds.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Place a teaspoon on center part biscuit to make indented for topping.

title: dill bread(servings: 4)
directions: *Creamed cottage cheese should be heated to lukewarm.

title: tony's chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook noodles for 6 to 8 minutes.
Use 4 1/2 quarts of water to cook chicken.
Boil chicken in large stock pot.
Let simmer for about 1 hour.
Cook vegetables in separate pot until they are done.
Don't throw away water from chicken.
Let chicken cool. Put vegetables in chicken water.
Add 2 or 3 chicken bouillon packets.
Cook for about 18 minutes and simmer for another 5. Enjoy!

title: peas and cashew salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss at last minute.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes in greased casserole.
Boil together next 4 ingredients until thick, stir constantly.
Pour over potatoes while hot.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Put cheese on top last few minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine and mix well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry yellow cake mix over top.
Drizzle 1 cup melted margarine over cake mix and top with 1 cup nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Check by inserting knife into cake.
If not done, turn oven off and leave in about 10 more minutes.
Check again before taking out.

title: chocolate cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, 1/2 cup butter and vanilla. Alternately beat in the sugar and 1/3 cup milk.
Blend in chocolate.
Remove 2 cups for frosting; cover and refrigerate.

title: chicken tetrazinni
directions: Cook noodles. Saute onions, peppers and celery in oleo. Stir in flour. Slowly cook until thick. Add seasonings and 1/2 cup cheese. Stir until melted. Add milk, pimentos, soup, chicken and noodles. Put in shallow baking dish (9 x 13). Cover with bread crumbs and remaining cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20
minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Melt cheese; add Ro-Tel.
Mix in chicken to cheese mixture. Add drained noodles.
Put into large casserole dish; top with chips.
Microwave on High for 1 minute, or put in oven until heated thoroughly.
Serve with salad and bread.
Can be eaten cold.

title: potato salad
directions: In a large kettle, put potatoes, cut in medium size bites. Cover with water.
Boil until tender.
Remove, drain and cool. Salt to taste.

title: vegetable and sandwich spread
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Warm to activate.
Puree all vegetables in food processor.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill for approximately 3 hours, or until mixture is well set.
Yields 3 cups.

title: crabby swiss cheese soup
directions: Chop up crabmeat; add along with diced onion and diced red pepper into milk and water.
Bring to a boil; be careful not to boil too long.
Reduce heat; add clam base, if desired, or salt to taste.
Dice Swiss cheese and add slowly while stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
It's important soup is hot when adding cheese.
Mix together cornstarch and water until thick and no lumps.
Add slowly to soup and simmer about 10 minutes or until desired thickness.
Repeat cornstarch and water mixture if needed.

title: pickled beets
directions: Leave 2-inch tops and roots on beets.
Wash.
Boil beets until tender, peel and cut into slices.
Put beets in a large pan.
Pour mixture over beets and let come to a boil.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Dip in candy chocolate.

title: chafing dish meat balls
directions: Combine ground
meat,
egg, onion and salt.
Keep separate. Combine and
heat chili sauce, lemon juice and jelly in a large skillet.
Shape meat mixture into small balls and drop into sauce. Simmer
until
brown.
Meat
balls
can be transferred to chafing dish and served warm with cocktail picks.

title: onion flavored rice
directions: Melt margarine in casserole.
Add rice and stir together.
Add soup and water (I also add sliced water chestnuts).
Cook on High in microwave until done, about 15 minutes.

title: cherry whip
directions: Mix and press into a 13 x 7-inch pan.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Press firmly in a sprayed 15 x 19-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 23 minutes, until golden brown.
Meanwhile, beat eggs, corn syrup, 1 1/2 cups sugar, butter and salt until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Immediately pour over the hot crust, spreading evenly. Bake 25 minutes or until filling is firm around the edges and slightly firm in the middle.
Cool completely.
Cut into 48 bars.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix sherbet in punch bowl.
Chop up in small pieces.
Add strawberry drink.
Blend strawberries in a blender, then add to punch mixture.
(Add another strawberry drink to fill punch bowl.)

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Prepare pudding mix using package directions reducing milk to 3 cups.
Fold in whipped topping.
Layer graham crackers and pudding mixture alternately in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, ending with graham crackers.
Melt chocolate in saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cool slightly.
Pour over graham crackers.
Chill, covered, until serving time.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: east harbor seafood pasta
directions: Start water for pasta.
In skillet, saute first five ingredients for 5 minutes; add seafood and cover for 12 minutes. Stir occasionally.
In saucepot, reduce cream with pepper and Old Bay; bring to a boil and stir until thickens.
Drop pasta; add reduced cream to seafood mixture in skillet.
Stir and toss with pasta.
Serve as side dish to grilled chicken or as its own dish with fresh parsley.

title: rice dessert
directions: Mix rice, pineapple, sugar and marshmallows and fold in whipped cream.
Put halved or whole cherries around in circle in bottom of glass mixture and pour in mixture.
Chill.
(Can be made previous night.)

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt margarine in top double boiler.
Drop in chocolate and melt.
Add sugar, gradually (4 tablespoons at a time).
Add salt. Add milk, gradually.
Water in double boiler must keep boiling. Last, add vanilla.
Cook until desired thickness, about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Can be stored in refrigerator as needed.
Makes 1 quart.

title: scotty bars
directions: Boil sugar and Karo; remove from stove and add peanut butter. Blend with Rice Krispies and spread on cookie sheet.

title: almond crescents
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add flour and salt.
Then add almonds.
Dip a little dough at a time in flour and roll between hands.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Powder with 10x sugar.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Simmer about 5 minutes or until clear.
Remove lemon slices and add blueberries.
Chill.
To serve, place ice cream on cantaloupe ring and top with blueberry sauce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk and egg.
Add salt and pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Place balls on baking sheet and bake until just done, about 20 minutes (*or use precooked meatballs from Sam's).

title: crispy chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine cereal, flour and seasonings. Place margarine in another bowl.
Dip chicken in margarine, then into cereal mixture.
Place in a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Drizzle with remaining margarine.
