Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until juices run clear.
Serves 4.

title: beefy deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks and add mayonnaise, mustard and relish.
Stir in dried beef and mix thoroughly.
Stuff egg whites.

title: percolator hot punch
directions: Use 30-cup percolator.
Add cider and cranberry juice in bottom of percolator.
In basket, add cinnamon, cloves and brown sugar and percolate until red light on percolator comes on.
Ready to serve.

title: spicy oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Lightly grease 15 x 10-inch pan. Combine dry ingredients. Dip chicken pieces in milk. Coat with dry ingredients. Place chicken, skin side up, in pan. Lightly brush with margarine. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until juices run clear when pierced with fork.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Dip cubed chicken in eggs and bread crumbs.
Heat oil in fryer (or deep saucepan suitable for frying) and deep fry breaded chicken until golden brown.
Combine duck sauce, orange juice, soy sauce and pineapple with 1/2 the syrup in separate saucepan and heat on low-medium flame, stirring occasionally.
When sauce begins to boil, remove from heat and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle on parsley flakes and serve over white rice.
Serves 5 to 7.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water. Let cool. Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten egg yolks; add 3/4 cup buttermilk alternately with flour.
Dissolve soda in remaining 1/4 cup buttermilk. Add salt, chocolate and vanilla. Finally fold in stiffly beaten whites. Bake in 350° oven until it springs back from touch.

title: jello cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.

title: baked fresh tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half.
Salt each half lightly and sprinkle with a pinch of sugar.
Combine breadcrumbs, melted butter, garlic, green onion, oregano, salt and pepper.
Mound over tomato halves, place under broiler just until golden on top, then bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, just until tomatoes are done but not collapsed.
Yields 8 servings.

title: double decker banana cups
directions: In a bowl, whisk together milk and pudding for 2 minutes. Fold in whipped topping. Refrigerate for at least 5 minutes. Divide half the pudding mix among 4 dessert dishes. Top with half the banana slices and remaining pudding mix. Sprinkle with crumbs. Top each with remaining banana slices and garnish with a cherry. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in large mixing bowl; stir in sugar, salt and 1/2 the flour.
Beat until smooth. Add egg and shortening. Beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Scrape sides of bowl and let rise in warm place until double in size (approximately 45 minutes).

title: broccoli and potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until brown.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces; drain. Discard all but 3 tablespoons fat.
Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick and chop onions.
Fry in 3 tablespoons reserved fat.
Add 1/2 cup water, cover and cook until tender.
Add red wine vinegar, sugar, salt and broccoli.
Cook until heated.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar and beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift rest of dry ingredients together.
Add sugar and add to mixture. Mix well.
Stir 1/2 cup of M&M's, more, if desired.
Set aside rest for decoration.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: horseradish salad (congealed)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add other ingredients and pour into large rectangle dish.
Refrigerate until set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Break frozen broccoli apart.
Mix ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until brown on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in butter, flour, vanilla, salt, sugar, syrup and pecans.
Mix well.
Prick bottoms of pie shells with fork.
Gently pour mixture into pie shells.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake about 40 minutes.
Makes 3 pies.

title: french quiche lorraine
directions: Spread cheese and other dry ingredients in pie shell.
Lightly beat eggs and milk.
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: green layered salad
directions: Place lettuce in bottom of Tupperware cold cut keeper and another small container, then add a layer of celery slices, then a layer of water chestnuts, next a layer of raw peas.
Add Miracle Whip on top.
Mix grated eggs and grated cheese and place on top of Miracle Whip; top with bacon bits.

title: zucchini bread #2
directions: Mix together and bake in a greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes about 2 small loaves.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In large bowl, combine all dry ingredients. Stir in buttermilk. Knead on floured board lightly. Shape dough into ball and place in greased 2-quart casserole. Cut 4-inch cross on top with floured back of knife. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: dolly darling's macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in lukewarm water.
Add salt, sugar and well beaten eggs.
Add oil or shortening and flour.
(Some flour takes up more moisture than others.)

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Pour broth over Fritos to wilt them.
Next, mix all together and put grated cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned and ingredients are done.

title: stuffed celery rings
directions: Cut top off celery; wash and dry each stalk.
Fill smallest stalk with cheese, then fill next smallest stalk; press firmly into first.
Continue filling and pressing stalks together until all celery is formed into a bunch.
Tie with string.
Chill.
To serve, cut crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.

title: carrot copper pennies
directions: Wash and scrape carrots and cut into rounds, about 1/4 inch thick.
Remove outer skin and cut onions into thin round slices. Remove seeds and white pithy part of bell pepper; cut into thin round slices.
Add carrots to 2 cups water in covered saucepan and cook over very high heat for 10 minutes.
Drain, cook and add to sliced rounds of onion and bell pepper in a large glass or stainless steel bowl.
Blend tomato soup, vegetable oil, sugar, vinegar, salt, black pepper, Worcestershire sauce, and mustard in another bowl.
Pour over vegetables and stir well.
Cover bowl and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Drain to serve.
These will keep two weeks or more refrigerated.
Yields 12 servings.

title: zesty italian crescent casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Stir in sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour hot meat mixture into ungreased 7 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine cheese and sour cream; spoon over meat.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Blend in melted and cooled chocolate or the Choco-bake and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each at medium speed.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.
At serving time, garnish with whipped cream and shaved chocolate.
Serves 8.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: 1st Layer:
Eight ounces cream cheese, mixed with 3 or 4 tablespoons taco sauce and garlic salt.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Beat eggs.
Microwave Cheez Whiz for 1 minute to soften.
Combine broccoli, Cheez Whiz, eggs, onion and milk.
Pour in pie shell.
Top pie with 4 teaspoons butter and 15 crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown turkey, onion and pepper together.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning mix.
Put in 9-inch pie pan, greased.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Mash with butter, salt and pepper.
Slightly beat egg and soak bread in egg.
Add slightly beaten egg, bread and onion; mix well.
Pour half of mixture in casserole dish; top with half of cheese.
Add remaining mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dutch pancakes(crepes)
directions: Put flour and salt in a bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Add the diluted (with a little milk) yeast.
Add 2 cups milk; mix to a smooth batter.
Add the rest of the milk.
Leave to rise for 3/4 hour.
Heat enough butter in a heavy skillet.
Pour in batter, enough to thinly cover bottom of pan.
Fry pancake on both sides. This happens rather quickly, so stand watch.
Keep repeating until all the batter is used.
Keep them warm and covered until serving. Serve with fruit, cheese, syrup, sugar ... the possibilities are endless!

title: szechuan steak
directions: Combine ingredients.
Marinate steak in plastic bag or shallow baking dish for 1 hour.
Remove meat and discard marinade.
Grill to desired doneness.
Serves 4.

title: lemon bread
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand for 5 minutes in pan, then pour 1/3 cup white sugar dissolved in juice of lemon.
Let stand until cool.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Arrange rhubarb in a greased baking dish. Sprinkle with the sugar and flour mixture. Mix remaining ingredients as for a pie crust. Spread over rhubarb. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together in crockpot.
Heat on low all day.

title: pineapple torte(torta de pina)
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Whip cream in electric mixer with the vanilla and powdered sugar to taste, until soft peaks form.
Drain pineapple; reserve 1/2 cup juice.
Cut pineapple into chunks; reserve 2 rings for garnish.
Slice cake rounds in half to obtain 4 layers.
Place 1 layer on cake platter; soak with some juice (you can add liqueur to the juice, if you like).
Spread some of the whipped cream and on top some pineapple.
Repeat with the other layers until done.
Cover top and sides of the Torte with cream; decorate with pineapple rings and maraschino cherries.

title: chickahominy house square biscuits(thanks to maxine henderson, williamsburg, va)
directions: Lard is used in these biscuits; if using other shortening, use 5 or 6 tablespoons.

title: pul-gogi(korean broiled beef)
directions: Put beef, sugar and oil into a bowl.
Mix well.
Combine soy sauce, pepper, chopped onion (including top), chopped garlic, sesame seed and flour.
Add to the meat mixture and mix well.
Let stand 15 minutes or overnight in refrigerator.
Broil on a charcoal fire or fry in a small amount of water; steam until meat is tender.
Serve hot with rice and vegetable salad.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In Dutch oven or large, heavy pot, make a roux of flour and oil.
Add onion, green pepper, celery, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Saute, uncovered, over medium heat until onion is transparent and soft.
Add tomato paste and saute 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Roll in nuts before serving.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cool. Drain all canned vegetables.
Place all in large bowl and pour oil mixture over.
Let stand several hours or overnight.

title: randy smokin' buck and doe
directions: Folks, this is the most tenderizing process for cooking wild meat.
Cooking temperature should reach about 150°.
Put meat on top of smoking rack, with coals white and with wet small limbs of wood on very bottom of smoker.

title: cakelike cornbread
directions: Beat eggs, milk and butter together.
Mix dry ingredients and then add liquid.
Fold in just until mixed.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: scalloped spinach
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Season with 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Turn into 9 1/2 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan (or similar pan).
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and outside comes out clean.

title: butterscotch pudding cake
directions: Mix pudding and eggs.
Add mixture to cake mix and beat with mixer.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Top with butterscotch chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. This cake freezes well.

title: bubble soap(yield: 1 quart)
directions: Fill quart bottle and use for children's bath.
May also be used to blow bubbles.

title: fresh salsa picant
directions: In medium bowl, combine ingredients; mix well.
Cover.
Chill. Serve with tortilla chips.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: green bean almandine
directions: Over low heat brown almonds in margarine until just brown; set aside.
Saute onion and water chestnuts until onions are clear.

title: broccoli-parmesan fettuccine
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water to cover for 3 minutes; drain and place ice cubes on top to cool.
Drain and set aside.
Cook fettuccine according to package directions; drain and place in large bowl.
Set aside.

title: bran muffins(12 muffins)
directions: Combine bran, flour and baking soda.
Combine butter and honey. Melt together in saucepan or microwave.
Combine buttermilk, eggs, butter and honey together; beat well.
Add to dry ingredients. Stir just to moisten dry ingredients.
Add raisins.
Divide among 12 greased or paper lined muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oat cake
directions: Add oats to boiling water; let stand 20 minutes.
Cream the shortening.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix the oats last. Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar pecans
directions: Boil cinnamon, salt, sugar and water to 240°.
Add the vanilla and pecan halves.
Spread on cookie sheet to cool.
Break apart when cool.

title: walnut chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. In a bowl, make a well and add in order:
oil, egg yolks, water and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until smooth in a large mixing bowl. Beat egg whites stiff.
Gradually pour mixture over egg whites, gently folding with rubber scraper just until blended.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 55 minutes at 325°.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix zucchini, eggs, parsley, cheese, and garlic.
Add in baking powder and then small amounts of flour at a time.
Mix well.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Turn each fritter as it browns.
Remove when brown and place on a paper towel.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Whip cream and add sugar, eggs (one at a time), milk and flavoring.
If you use any kind of fruit, reduce the amount of flavoring.
Pour into ice cream freezer canister and follow manufacturers directions.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in large mixing bowl, including bread cubes.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Pour into buttered casserole; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cheddar cheese pie
directions: Toss cheese with flour.
Add eggs, milk, ham and seasonings; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.
Garnish with parsley and pimento strips as desired. Serves 6.

title: rotini salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender; rinse with cold water.
Chop green onions, green peppers and sweet pickles.
Mix vegetables with pasta.
Pour dressing over mixture and mix well.
Chill until serving.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain marinade from 1 jar artichokes into a skillet.
Drain the other jar and discard marinade.
Chop all artichokes and set aside.
Add onions and garlic to skillet; saute until clear.
Beat eggs.
Add crumbs and seasonings.
Stir in cheese, parsley, artichokes and onion mixture.
Turn into a greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool in pan.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve hot or cold.

title: grandma's raspberry dessert
directions: Heat raspberries with water, sugar and lemon juice.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup cold water, then stir into raspberries and cook until thickened; cool.
Melt marshmallows in milk over boiling water.
Then cool thoroughly.
Whip cream or topping mix and fold into marshmallow mixture, which has been cooled.

title: grandma's ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg and molasses. Roll in 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place far apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or 15 minutes for crispy.

title: okra soup
directions: Combine
okra,
corn,
tomatoes, salt, pepper, potatoes and sugar.
Cook
until potatoes are done over a medium fire. With the flour and the water, make a smooth mixture and add to the
soup mixture until medium thick.
Serves 10 to 12.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry-orange-banana smoothie
directions: Mix in a blender until very smooth and enjoy. Makes 2 servings.

title: coolrise sweet dough
directions: Use this recipe for Mexican Sweet Rolls.
Yield:
30 rolls.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch thick slices.
Line an ungreased 14-inch pizza pan or cookie sheet with slices overlapping slightly.
(Or roll out dough on cookie sheet.)
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes; cool.

title: chocolate cherry decadence
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Toast almonds about 10 minutes, being careful not to burn them.
Cool.
Line a 9-inch round cake pan with plastic wrap.
Melt 1 cup chocolate chips and 1/4 cup cream over lowest heat.
Remove from heat and stir in almonds.
Pour into plastic lined pan and spread over bottom.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash the green peppers. Drain well. Salt cavities lightly. Combine beef, rice, water, onion, salt and 1/4 cup ketchup.
Mix well.
Stuff green peppers. Arrange stuffed peppers in crock-pot. Pour in ketchup and water. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours (high 3 hours).
Serve on a bed of rice and pour tomato sauce over top.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Halve tomatoes.
Trim ends so they lie flat in pan.
Place in buttered pan.
Mix all other ingredients and melted butter.
Pat on tomatoes firmly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves six.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut off stem ends of peppers; remove seeds.
Boil 5 minutes in lightly salted water; drain.
Crumble crackers in mixing bowl. Add diced Cheddar cheese.
Pour enough boiling water over mixture to moisten well.
Cover and let stand until cheese is melted, but not cold.
Mix well with spoon.
Stuff pepper shells.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix the potatoes, onion, celery, pickles, mango and eggs.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Make a brine that will bear up an egg. Pour over the pickles in a stone jar (glass crock). Let stand 7 days. Take out and wash in cold water. Cut pickles lengthwise.

title: pistachio coffee cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, eggs, nuts and water.
Mix with wire whisk.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Spray Bundt or tube pan and alternate layers of batter and filling, ending with filling on top.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Drain.
Cook sausage until crumbly. Pour off fat.
Stir in mushrooms and soup.
Add to rice.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven 60 minutes. Serves 4.

title: almond granola
directions: Stir dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Mix liquid ingredients and pour over dry mixture.
Mix well.
Bake on cookie sheet about 1 hour at 250° to 300° until dry and toasted lightly.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well blended. Beat egg into mixture. Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Add to mixture blending well. Stir in chocolate chips and pecans. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough 3 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies. Let cool.

title: marinated chicken breast
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir well and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate chicken for 2 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade. Grill over hot coals about 8 minutes on each side.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin log with cream cheese filling
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Pour onto greased (may use spray grease) 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet and sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn onto a tea-type flat towel, well covered with confectioners sugar.
Top with wax paper.
Roll entire mixture (including towel and wax paper) from side to side. After cooling, unroll and remove wax paper.
Cream the second group of ingredients together until smooth.
Spread with cream cheese filling and re-roll.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: cheerwine ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into ice cream freezer and finish filling with milk.

title: fig nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking pan.
Beat eggs until foamy; beat in sugar and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in figs and nuts.
Spread batter in pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes; cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: pork chop and sauerkraut casserole
directions: Place in layers in oblong baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: tennessee quick frosting
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; add sugar and milk.
Stir constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Boil hard for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and nuts.
Leave cake in pan (9 x 13-inch).
Spread frosting on slightly warm cake.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine in blender for 3 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan; cover.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: icing
directions: Boil flour in milk until thick and let get cold.
Mix all ingredients together and beat with mixer.

title: lifesaver soup
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook all ingredients until cabbage and celery are tender.

title: berry banana shake
directions: Cut banana into chunks.
Place all ingredients into blender and blend until smooth.
Makes 6 (5 ounce) servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: italian beef sandwich(chicago style)
directions: This makes a great change of pace leftover use for beef.
It is a Chicago tradition.
If using uncooked meat, cut into 1-inch cubes, brown and cook 1 1/2 hours in a covered Dutch oven or skillet, seasoning to taste.
When using leftovers, cube to 1-inch.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half, lengthwise.
Carefully remove yolks and mash in bowl.
Combine mashed egg yolks, relish, mayonnaise, pimiento, lemon juice, mustard, salt and pepper and mix until well blended.
Fill egg white halves with mixture; divide between the six halves.
Chill before serving.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Sprinkle olive oil over top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: pudding eclairs
directions: Mix pudding with milk and cook according to package directions.
Cover surface with wax paper and refrigerate.
When cool, fold in whipped topping.
Bring 6 Tbsp. butter and water to a boil.
Reduce heat and rapidly stir in flour.
Cook and stir until mixture leaves sides of pan, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat in eggs, one at a time, until satiny.
Form 5 x 1-inch strips of dough with spoon on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 425 degrees for 20 minutes, reduce heat to 350 and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut tops off shells and fill with pudding; replace tops.
Melt chocolate and butter over low heat. Remove from heat and add sugar, salt and milk.
Spread over tops of shells.
Some will run down the sides.

title: beer battered onion rings
directions: Beat mixture of all ingredients except onion rings.
Put onion rings in batter.
Deep fry until done.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all together.
Add milk until thick.
Should be able to be dropped off spoon.
Add to chicken soup.

title: puerto rican chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken pieces until flat; cut into strips.
Sprinkle spice mixture onto chicken pieces.
Wrap pieces of chicken around strips of cheese.
Then wrap slice of bacon around each piece (making roll-ups).
Mix liquid together and pour over roll-ups. Bake uncovered at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: asparagus with rosemary aioli
directions: In a food processor work bowl, process oil, garlic, rosemary and balsamic vinegar for 30 seconds.
Let mixture sit 5 minutes.

title: double chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling, milk, chips and butter in a saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice. Pour into shell and chill 3 hours.
Garnish with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chocolate curls or grated chocolate.

title: tuna surprise(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Drain; flake tuna.
Add all ingredients; stir.
Mound on crackers, Triscuits or Toast Pointe.
Broil and serve.

title: hot cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix.
Spread about 1/4 cup of mix on a slice of bread and top with second slice.
Trim crust and slice in fourths after desired number of sandwiches have been prepared.
(Mix will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.)
Bake at 425° until light brown.

title: lo-cal chicken stew
directions: Remove skin and cut up chicken.
Brown in skillet over medium heat.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serves 5.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef and dry ingredients.
Shape into 12 meatballs. Brown in cooking oil, turning frequently.
Pour in tomato sauce and water; stir lightly.
Cover; simmer for approximately 45 minutes, stirring only occasionally.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bake pie shell according to package directions and let cool. Mix chicken, soup, drained vegetables and 1/2 can of onion rings. Pour in pie shell and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Add rest of onion rings, spread over the top of pie for the last 5 minutes of baking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hawaiian pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple (save juice for glaze). Stir baking mix, flour and soda.
Beat sugar, sour cream, oleo and vanilla together for 2 minutes.
Add flour mixture and beat 1 minute longer.
Stir in pineapple and rum.
Turn in well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and spoon over 1/2 glaze over cake.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Turn out on plate and spoon on remaining glaze.
Cool before cutting.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cut in shortening until like coarse cornmeal.
Combine juice and rind with egg.
Mix at high speed until foamy and add to dry mix.
Mix just enough to dampen. Carefully fold in chopped nuts and cranberries.
Spread in loaf pan, corners and sides a little higher than center.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pan to cool.
Tastes better if stored a couple of days.

title: low carbohydrate cream cheese pie
directions: Whip cream cheese with mixer.
Add eggs, Splenda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.	Cool and put in refrigerator.
Total pie is 18 carbohydrates.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream softened oleo and white syrup.
Add vanilla and sugar. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Work dough around drained cherries into walnut size balls.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Place toothpicks through covered cherries and dip into chocolate mixture and place on wax paper.

title: dandelion salad with hot bacon dressing
directions: In a deep skillet, fry the bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
In a small bowl, combine the cornstarch, salt and sugar.
Add the eggs, stirring with a whisk until smooth, then slowly add the vinegar.
Blend milk with egg mixture and slowly add to the bacon fat in the skillet.
Return skillet to the stove and place on low to medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil and continue to boil for one minute, stirring continuously with a whisk.
Break the bacon into bits and add half of the bacon to the dressing.
Save the rest for garnishing salads.

title: almond crust cherry cream pie
directions: Mix together and follow package directions to bake a 9-inch pie shell.
Cool.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, powdered sugar and oleo and spread on round sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together and spread onto cooled crust.
Make paste with cornstarch and some berries, then add rest of berries and cook until thick.
Let cool, then spread on cream cheese layer. Put Cool Whip on top when ready to serve.

title: raisin cakes
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add rest of ingredients, cooking raisins until soft and adding to batter last.
Bake in muffin tins at 375°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Bring sugar and Karo syrup to a boil.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter, then Rice Krispies.
Roll into small balls.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed until sugar melts; cool.
Mix cabbage, onions and carrots with cooled vinegar; add salt and chill well.
It may be stored in refrigerator for at least a week.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Separate fillets.
Heat oven to 500°.
Oil a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Dip fish in combination of buttermilk, salt, pepper and thyme, then in a mixture of crumbs and parsley to coat both sides.
Lay the fillets in prepared baking dish in a single layer if possible.
Drizzle with cooking oil.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until fish is golden and flakes easily with a fork.
Do not turn.
Serve immediately.

title: classic potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Gently stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: peanut butter snack
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour cereal into large mixing bowl.
Heat peanut butter and margarine in small saucepan until boiling, stirring occasionally.
Pour over cereal; toss until evenly coated. Spread in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from oven.
Stir in Goldfish crackers, pretzels, raisins and peanuts.
Spread on waxed paper; cool 2 hours.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 8 cups snack.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook salad dressing, sugar and vinegar until they become thick and clear.
Let cool for approximately 2 hours.
Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Mix onion and broccoli pieces.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble into broccoli mixture.
Pour cooled dressing over broccoli mixture and toss to mix.
Add raisins, if desired.

title: frozen pineapple yogurt
directions: In a food processor, puree pineapple and banana.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Stir in yogurt and maple syrup.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and pour into pan.
In a separate bowl, mix the sugar and cocoa.
Pour on top of the other ingredients.
Pour the boiling water on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: christmas wafers
directions: Mix well and chill in 1/2-inch thick patties wrapped in Saran Wrap.

title: jimmy's "hot" wings sauce
directions: Melt margarine.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Form into a ball or log.
Sprinkle with chili powder or roll in chopped nuts.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken wing dings
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in an oven-proof glass baking dish and cover.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Line the bottom of a large glass bowl with chunks of angel food cake.
Mix the dry Jello with the sliced strawberries.
Pour over cake chunks.
Slice the bananas over the strawberries.
Pour the prepared pudding over the bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: mom's favorite stew
directions: Cook in a crock-pot or can be cooked in a pressure cooker. Place meat, potatoes and then onions.
Salt and pepper over the top.
Add 1 cup water and place on stove and pressure at 15 pounds for 15 minutes.
Remove lid after pressure is reduced.
Add 2 cans mushroom soup and water.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bangus fish steak
directions: Mince onions and tomatoes, then mix.
Get 1/2 of the mixed tomatoes and onions, spread in a frying pan.
Place, on top of the Bangus, the remaining half of the onions and tomatoes.
Pour on the mixed vinegar and soy sauce.
Cover the pan.
Cook over low fire until the fish and ingredients are well cooked.
Pour on the calamansi juice and let boil for a very short while.
For seasoning, add 1 tablespoon oil and a dash of Accent.

title: hot dogs
directions: You put the wieners in a pot, then you take them out and wash them off.
Put wiener in the hog dog buns.
Put mustard, ketchup and chili on hot dogs.
And eat it.
The daddy does the dishes and the kids go to bed when it's dark.

title: frank green's mushroom sauce
directions: Slice mushrooms; add to melted butter.
Add other ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes over low heat.
Serve hot over grilled steak.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Fry potatoes with onions until brown.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients in frying pan.
Bake at 400° about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and milk over low heat.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Continue cooking until thick (stir constantly).
Remove from heat and fold in margarine and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the soup, sour cream and onion.
Pour over cooked chicken. Sprinkle crushed Ritz crackers over the chicken.
Drizzle melted butter over the cracker topping.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: tonkatsu
directions: Slash fatty parts of chops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and set aside for 2 or 3 minutes.
Dredge meat in flour.
Dip in beaten egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Leave for 2 or 3 minutes.

title: beef green bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Add beans with part of liquid and soup.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Top with grated cheese.

title: buttermilk coffee cake
directions: Combine oleo, brown sugar, white sugar, flour and cinnamon. Take out 1/2 cup of this mixture and mix with pecans for topping. Set aside.

title: cheese danish
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 pan.
Unroll rolls in bottom of pan.
Mix cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Spread mixture on top of rolls.
Spread 2nd pkg of rolls on top.
MIx nuts and sugar and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add oil, eggs, vanilla, crushed pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Mix with spoon (do not beat).
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool in pan.

title: white beans with garlic, spinach and tomatoes
directions: Heat the olive oil in a saute pan.
When hot, add the garlic and onions.
Continue cooking over medium to low heat for 10 minutes.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of water if the onions begin to stick.
Add the chopped spinach, cover, and continue to cook for 5 minutes.
Remove the lid, and add chopped tomatoes, beans and thyme.
Heat through.
Serve plain or as a topping for crostini. Makes 6 servings.

title: pound cake 1
directions: Note:
Best if ingredients are at room temperature.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast in mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Combine milk and butter in saucepan.
Heat until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and 1 cup flour and beat 2 minutes.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough on floured surface.
Knead until smooth, about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Make into rolls.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stir-fry turkey or chicken
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Cook 2 cups rice (4 cups water).
Prepare vegetables and meat strips.
Heat oil in large skillet or wok.
Add celery, mushrooms and onions.
Stir-fry until thoroughly heated.
Add liquid and bring to a boil.
Stir until mixture has boiled, clears and thickens.
Add meat.
Bring to a boil.
Thoroughly heat.
Serve over rice.

title: reuben dip
directions: Combine all together.
Add mayonnaise until it gets to a tuna fish consistency.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Ritz crackers or rye bread.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble hamburger into bottom of casserole dish.
Season to taste.
Spread mushroom soup over top.
Arrange Tater Tots over top of soup.
Bake casserole in a 350° oven for one hour.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges, pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Mix all ingredients together well and chill.
Enjoy!
Yields 6 servings.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Pour rice in buttered baking dish. Combine soup and boiling water.
Mix well.
Pour over rice.
Place cut up chicken pieces on top. Sprinkle dried onion soup over chicken. Cover tightly and bake at 325° to 350° for approximately 2 hours.
(Longer baking to 2 1/2 hours won't hurt.)
Do not peek!

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and add cheese, sour cream, soups, onion and chestnuts.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Spread on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: one dish dinner
directions: Layer potatoes, onions and carrots in baking dish (cake pan size).
Put meat on top and cover with soup.
Cover with foil or cover of dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion, then drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce. Mix tomato sauce into beef and heat until hot and bubbly.

title: mother's forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites and sugar until fluffy and stiff peaks form.
Fold in chips, extract and food colorings. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Put in oven.
Turn off oven immediately.
Leave in oven overnight (forgotten cookies).

title: chicken chunk casserole
directions: Boil chicken (whole) until tender.
Cool, then take meat from bones, removing and discarding skin.
Save water and boil spaghetti in it for extra flavor.

title: lovely lemon cake
directions: Mix cake mix and Jell-O gelatin.
(If you have whisk beaters on your mixer, use them to get the gelatin well mixed in the cake mix.)
Add eggs, water and oil.
Pour into a 13 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake as directed on cake mix box.
(I like to use Duncan Hines Lemon Supreme cake mix).
Remove from oven and pierce with fork all over top of cake.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Place both chips in microwaveable bowl. Heat 1-1/2 minutes. Stir. Heat another 1-1/2 minutes. When chips are melted completely, mix in nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. If they do not set in 1 hour, refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: simple potatoes
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and place in 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine crushed corn flakes and some melted oleo on the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Slice chicken in thin strips; salt and pepper.
Cook in approximately 3 tablespoons oil in wok or large heavy pot until no longer pink.
Remove and set aside.
Slice cabbage, onions and celery in strips.
Put in pot with bouillon cubes and enough water to cover.
Simmer until vegetables are almost tender; add chicken and enough corn starch to thicken.
Continue simmering until vegetables are soft.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: beebee's sweet relish
directions: Grind tomatoes.
Add salt and set aside for 1 hour.
Grind onions and peppers.
Add spices, sugar and vinegar and add to tomatoes. Set for another hour.
Drain.
Cook on medium heat for 25 minutes.
Put in pint jars.
Makes 16 pints.
Or put in half gallon jar and refrigerate, using as needed.

title: kraut salad
directions: Bring sugar, oil and vinegar to boil.
Drain kraut and pimentos.
Add remaining ingredients and pour hot sugar mixture over kraut mixture and refrigerate.

title: roast turkey
directions: Combine the garlic, rosemary, pepper and salt in a blender. Turn on.
Add the oil.
Blend until coarsely chopped.
Spread half the garlic mixture over the inside of turkey.
Re-roll the turkey. Tie firmly with string every two inches to return the meat to its original log shape.
Spread on the remaining mixture.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Bring broth to boil in large pan.
Add broccoli.
Cover and cook until done.
Add chicken, soups, cheese, salt and pepper. Bring to a slow boil.
Turn off heat.
Add Minute rice (not too much rice).
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter. Add flour, onion and garlic powders, salt and pepper, sugar, cheese, pimento, sour cream and water chestnuts in saucepan. Cook until the cheese is melted. Remove from heat and cool. Pour over green beans. Sprinkle with French fried onions. Bake about 15 minutes at 375°.

title: rhubarb cake #1
directions: Mix brown sugar, oleo, egg and buttermilk in mixer.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and rhubarb.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with the mixture made with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Bake at 350° until done.
Punch holes in cake with fork.

title: peanut butter bites
directions: In a heavy saucepan, bring milk, shortening and peanut butter to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add raisins, vanilla and Equal.
Mix well.
Work in oats, a cup at a time.
Form into small balls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Chill.
Keep refrigerated and covered.

title: cracker snack
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix with crackers until well coated.
Spread onto baking sheet.
Bak at 250° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container, Tupperware or Ziploc bag.

title: quick easy curry
directions: If apple is not available, add 1/2 cup raisins.

title: tuna-chip casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup crushed chips for garnish.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Border with remaining chips.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until hot. Makes 4 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with pepperoni.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Heat in pot on stove until warm. Serve with favorite meats or poultry, hot or cold.

title: noodle kugel *
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Beat eggs and add to butter mixture with cream cheese and beat well.
Add other ingredients (except noodles and cinnamon) and mix together.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put in noodles (scatter throughout).
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Refrigerate overnight (up to 24 hours).
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes, then at 350° for one hour.
Can be frozen and reheated; also good cold.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water with enough sugar to sweeten.
When raisins are soft, thicken as for raisin pie.
Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice, 2 teaspoons butter and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Remove from heat.
Cream brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time; continue beating and add milk alternately with dry ingredients.

title: almond delight fruit cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together with only 1/2 cup of crushed cereal.
Set in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Take out of refrigerator and form into a ball.
Roll in remaining cereal and refrigerate.

title: pears baked in red wine
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pierce bottom of each pear with a clove.
Place pears on sides in deep casserole dish.
Combine wine, sugar and water.
Pour over pears.
Syrup need not cover pears.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Turn pears over carefully. Uncover and bake for about 30 minutes more.
Test for doneness with fork or toothpick.
Serve hot or cold in wine syrup, topped with whipped cream.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper. Mix in drained tuna and soup. Add broccoli, peas or green beans. Add rice or noodles and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mim maw's chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk in heavy saucepan.
Cook and stir constantly, letting boil about 10 to 15 minutes on medium heat until it reaches the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Beat together and let cool, beating often. Spread on any layer cake.

title: peanut crispies
directions: Combine sugar and Karo syrup in medium saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, stirring until creamy.
Add chow mein noodles and stir until coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.

title: cool whip fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: applesauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cover; bring to a boil. Reduce to low and simmer until apples are tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes four servings.

title: slush punch
directions: Jello and Kool-Aid can be any flavor.
Bring water to a boil and dissolve jello. Add the Kool-Aid and the sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice to the mixture and freeze.
When ready to serve, let mixture stand at room temperature until mix can be chopped into chunks and is slushy.
Add club soda and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in crust.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.

title: smothered garden vegetables
directions: Cut bacon in pieces.
Slice all vegetables (no need to peel unless you prefer).
Brown bacon.
Add onion and bell pepper; saute awhile.
Add other vegetables, seasoning to taste.
Smother down, stirring often, until potatoes are tender.

title: lazy day pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl and add milk.
Make into a batter; add margarine.
Pour batter into baking dish.
Distribute fruit evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
You can use any fruit.

title: baked asparagus and mushroom omelet
directions: Cook fresh asparagus, mushrooms and green onions in a small amount of boiling water for about 7 minutes or until tender.
(Or, cook frozen asparagus, mushrooms and green onions according to asparagus package directions.)
Drain.

title: squirrel with rice and tomatoes
directions: In a large pot, brown meat in sauce and butter.
Add water and cubes; simmer until meat is tender.
Add rice, tomatoes (juice from tomatoes), salt, pepper and crushed red pepper flakes.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes, until rice is done.

title: virginia spoon bread
directions: Mix the following ingredients in the same pan in which it is to be baked:
corn meal, sugar and salt.
In a hole in the middle, put the shortening.
Over this, pour the boiling water and mix well.
Add the eggs, milk and baking powder; stir well.
Stand pan in hot water and bake at 350°.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Boil raisins in water until the water evaporates.
Combine all other ingredients and beat well.
Bake in a 350° oven about 25 to 30 minutes. Bake in two loaf pans, well greased and floured.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese and melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients except rolls. Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Put mixture into each roll and roll up.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: texas pin wheels
directions: Combine cream cheese, green onions, dressing mix.
Spread on tortillas.	Sprinkle olives, chilies and pimentos.	Roll each tortilla tight in wax paper, then plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight. Slice into pieces about 8-inches each roll.
Makes about 30 to 40 pieces.
May be frozen up to 3 months.
Looks great for Christmas!

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: layered cranberry apple dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add drink.
Measure out 2 cups and chill it until slightly thickened.
Add cranberry sauce to the remaining Jell-O/drink mix.
Blend well and let it chill until thickened.
Blend Cool Whip into the 2 cups of slightly jelled Jell-O.
Add the apple.
Pour mixture into a 7 to 8 cup bowl and chill until firm.
When the creamy layer is firm and the sauce mixture is thickened, spoon the sauce mixture over the creamy layer.
Chill 3 hours until set.

title: methodist cake
directions: Bake the cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.
Mix the cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk.
Mix with prepared pudding and beat good. Put the pineapple on cake.
Put Cool Whip on top of the pudding mixture.
Top with ground nutmeats.

title: famous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Measure 5 cups oatmeal and put small amounts in blender or food processor to form a powder.
Add oatmeal powder, flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder to sugar mixture.
Stir well.
Grate the candy bar and add in with chocolate chips.
Shape dough into small balls and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen. Great for large gatherings!

title: bro. turner's peanut brittle
directions: Cook slowly first 4 ingredients until mixture spins a thread and forms firm ball in cold water.
Stir in baking soda.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and beat eggs. Combine all ingredients. Place in greased dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake bread for approximately 20 minutes (until golden brown).
Serves 12.

title: oven stew
directions: Cook in Dutch oven with lid on for 4 hours at 250°.
Two hours before stew is done, add potatoes, green beans and carrots.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown onion in margarine. Add beef, onion, celery, tomato soup and mushroom soup. Salt and pepper to taste. Break spaghetti in short lengths and cook. Drain and put in the bottom of a 3-quart casserole dish. Layer beef, sauce and grated cheese. Top with mushroom soup. Garnish with olives. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Place chicken on waxed paper.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness. Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip meat into eggs and roll in crumbs.
Brown in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Cover; chill for at least 2 hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Drain.
Can be served as a dip with tortilla chips or in a lettuce cup as a salad.
Makes 7 cups.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 5 minutes after each egg.
Pour into cooled pie shell. Chill 2 hours.
Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with grated Hershey bar, if desired.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and eggs in saucepan; cook until melted. Add flavoring to taste.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, checking.
Continue cooking and checking until done. (It will look like jelly and be slightly glazed when done.)

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Bake in a covered roaster. Brown chops in roaster on top of stove.
Pour off any fat that accumulates.
Cook Minute rice while chops are browning.
Place chops in bottom of roaster.
Put 2 small (or 1 large) slice onion on each chop. Spoon rice over chops, mounding on each chop.
Pour tomato sauce over all. Sprinkle green beans over all, using liquid in can. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Check to see if some water should be added, about 1 cup, if needed.
Continue baking another 30 minutes. Serve 6.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Bring first five ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer five minutes.
Pour half of sauce into a large, shallow baking dish.
Add potatoes.
Top with remaining sauce.
Bake in 350° oven, basting often, for 20 minutes.

title: granny's rancho beans
directions: Brown the ground chuck and onion.
Drain.
Add all the beans and their juices, ketchup, and water.
Stir well.
Bring to a boil then simmer about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch and boil until thick; cool.
Combine cooled mixture with strawberries and pour into a baked pie shell.

title: cool mint chocolate pie
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and peppermint extract.
Beat until well blended.

title: no-roll sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given and form into balls about the size of walnuts.
Dip each in sugar and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit wreaths
directions: Beat butter creamy.
Add sugar; beat in egg.
Stir all ingredients together.
Chill, shape and bake at 350° until done.

title: rigatoni and asparagus
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook rigatoni until barely tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Add asparagus to pot for the last 3 to 4 minutes of cooking time so that asparagus comes out crisp-tender.
Drain water off and run cold water over rigatoni and asparagus in pot.
Drain well.
Add marinara sauce, sour cream, vinegar, scallions, basil, salt and pepper to pasta and asparagus in pot.
Toss to mix well.
Heat through 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: bacon and chutney
directions: Crumble bacon and mix with chutney.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Scoop out centers of zucchini; cut this into small pieces. Place into a bowl.
Add the beaten eggs, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir and spoon into shells.
Bake.
Put 1/2 cup water in casserole before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, covered, and for 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Shape into ball and roll in finely chopped pecans.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together; bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and blend well.
Stir in oatmeal.
Mix well, then drop on waxed paper by teaspoons.
Let stand until firm.

title: french chocolate chiffon pie
directions: When chocolate is cold, mix with butter and sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add the 3 eggs, one at a time, each to be beaten for 5 minutes (whole process takes 15 minutes).
Add vanilla.
Put into baked pie shell and refrigerate overnight.
May be served as is or with whipped cream.

title: pee wee sandwiches
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onion together.
Add salt, pepper and cheese to meat.
Cut buns in half and scoop on.
Crumble 1/2 of bread into meat mixture.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Spoon mixture into buns. Brush garlic butter over.
Heat at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix and shape into balls.

title: cream of wheat cornbread
directions: Bake in an iron skillet at 425° for about 25 minutes.

title: cold tuna dip
directions: Drain off all of the oil from the tuna and rinse the tuna well with hot water.
Combine all of the ingredients; mixing well. Serve the dip cold.
This is better if done in advance.

title: corn creole
directions: Saute chopped onion in bacon fat with finely chopped garlic. Add corn.
Add egg beaten with milk.
Add corn meal and season to taste with salt, red and black pepper.
Stir over medium heat until mixture is thick.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Place in oven to keep warm.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: carrots lyannaise
directions: Pare carrots and cut in julienne strips, about 3 x 1/4-inch. Dissolve bouillon in the 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add carrots and cook, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Cook sugar and pineapple (undrained) for 5 minutes.
Add cool water and jello.
Dissolve and let congeal, then add pecans and cheese.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold into jello mixture.
Pour into a dish and chill.
Keeps well in refrigerator for days. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown meat and onions in large pan. Drain. Mix all ingredients together except pepperoni and cheese. Put in baking dish (large). Cover with pepperoni and cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with garlic bread.

title: lemon carrot cookies
directions: In a bowl, beat together the butter and sugar until creamy. Beat in lemon extract, vanilla, egg and carrot.
Stir together the flour and dry ingredients.
Add to butter mixture, then the nuts. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Place about 1/2-inch apart.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until edges are brown.
Cool on rack.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: original nestle toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by level measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1 or 2 teaspoons to taste per cup of hot water.

title: easy fried rice
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: barbecued pork and bean bake
directions: Place beans in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange pork chops on top of beans.
For each chop dash with salt and pepper. Spread lightly with mustard.
Sprinkle with about 1 1/2 tablespoons of brown sugar.
Spread with about 1 1/2 tablespoons of catsup. With toothpick, attach 1 slice of onion and 1/2 slice of lemon on top of each chop.
Bake in a slow 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours or until chops are fork-tender.

title: rib-eye barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients and simmer in cooking pot. Do not boil.
Simmer
for	20 minutes.
Strain sauce to remove fennel seed, if necessary.

title: mint jelly
directions: Mix juice and sugar.
Boil rapidly.
When mix is near jelly stage add mint extract and green food coloring.
Makes 4 (4 ounce) glasses.

title: poor man's hamburger stew
directions: Peel and wash potatoes; cut into bite-sized chunks.
boil in clean water and a little salt until just done.
As the potatoes are cooking, in another large pot or huge skillet brown ground beef.
When just brown add diced onion and cook until onion is clear (at this time if health conscience drain fat from mixture). Add beans; stir when beans have heated through and add potato chunks. Stir.
Now is the time to add whatever spices you desire, my favorites are: garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste and chili powder.
Simmer for about 20 minutes so the flavors mingle.

title: frozen yogurt cookie pie
directions: In small bowl, combine crushed cookies and butter.
Mix well. Press in bottom only of 9-inch pie plate.
Stand 18 whole cookies up around edges, pressing slightly into crust mixture.
Freeze 20 minutes until cold.
Carefully spread softened ice cream over crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Cover; freeze at least 2 hours or overnight.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesies
directions: Combine flour, butter and sour cream in mixing bowl; mix well. Divide into 4 portions; chill until firm.
Roll out dough, one portion at a time, to 12 x 6-inch.
Sprinkle with salt and 3/4 cup shredded cheese.
Starting with 12-inch side, roll up, jelly roll fashion.
Seal edges.
Place, seam side down, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using sharp knife, cut rolls halfway at inch intervals. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes about 45 appetizers.

title: crackerjack cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits the size of a saucer.
Put about 1/4 of an apple (sliced or the whole quarter) in the center of the biscuit. Sprinkle on some of the cinnamon mixture.
Add a small pat of butter.
Bring all four corners together and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
When done, take out and pour on sauce that's made of 1 cup sugar, 1 stick of butter, the water and the cornstarch. Delicious!

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and add pineapple. Refrigerate until partially congealed.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and condensed milk thoroughly.
Add to gelatin mixture. Stir in nuts and chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce.

title: mint tea
directions: Add sugar
to water and tea stems.
Boil a few minutes; turn off heat
and
let	stand
10 minutes, then put through a cloth or strainer and squeeze out stems.
Add lemon and enough water to make a gallon.
Chill and serve.

title: stroganoff with hungarian taste
directions: Coat meat with flour.
Fry in skillet over medium-high heat in margarine until no longer pink.
Remove from skillet.
In the same skillet, cook mushrooms and onions in remaining margarine until tender.
Return meat to skillet; add broth, tomato juice and steak sauce.
Bring it to a boil and reduce heat to low.
Cover and let simmer for 20 minutes or until meat is tender.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Wash broccoli and cauliflower; cut into small flowerets.
In large bowl, mix broccoli, cauliflower, onion and cheese.
Blend mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli-cauliflower mixture; toss until all ingredients are well coated.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Right before serving, add crumbled bacon and toss well.
Serves 8.

title: cube steak and mushroom gravy
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Trim off fat.
Salt and pepper meat.
Roll in flour and brown on both sides in a frying pan.
Put meat in a casserole dish.
Put cream of mushroom soup into frying pan with meat drippings and add water.
Bring to a full boil.
Pour over steak and sprinkle onion soup over this.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cover while baking.

title: breakfast surprise
directions: Have all ingredients ready before you start.
Divide crescent rolls into eight parts at scored places.
Spread each one with butter.
Divide cream cheese into 8 equal parts, place dab onto each square.
Spread evenly.
Place piece of banana at top of each. Top with jam.
Carefully roll bottom over.
Dampen edges and seal good.
Place on baking sheet.
Brush tops with beaten eggs.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry waldorf
directions: Grind the cranberries and combine with the marshmallows and sugar. Cover and chill overnight. Add apples, grapes, walnuts and salt. Fold in whipped cream. Chill. Serve in large bowl or individual lettuce cups.
Garnish with clusters of green grapes and fresh cranberries, if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° in a jelly roll pan for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with chocolate frosting recipe.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine oats, peanut butter, vanilla and cocoa.
Make a syrup of sugar, milk and butter.
Boil sugar mixture for 1 minute.
Pour syrup on oat mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and let stand for 1 hour or more.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix.
Pour half of batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
While cake is baking, melt margarine, milk and caramels.
When cake is done, pour caramel mixture over it.
Sprinkle over mixture nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour remaining batter over all and return to oven.
Bake 20 minutes more or until done.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute onion, celery, pepper, chopped stems from mushrooms and seasoning in margarine until softened. Add shrimp. Mix into cracker crumbs and stuff mushrooms. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: *romanian marble sponge cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add milk, then add flour, baking powder and vanilla. Beat the egg whites stiff. Gently fold into batter. Fold in the nuts. Add cocoa to 1/4 of the batter.
Grease a large tube pan well.
Pour cocoa mixture and then add the white mixture on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: hush puppies
directions: Blend egg, milk, onion and water.
Set aside.
Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add egg mixture; stir to moisten.
Drop batter into deep fat (heated to 375°) for 2 minutes.
Turn once.
Yields 24.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° in two tube pans.
Line pans with wax paper or foil.
Start in cold oven!!

title: vegetable skillet supper
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove; drain on paper towels and crumble.
Saute hamburger and onion in 2 tablespoons bacon fat until meat is browned.
Add tomatoes, water, salt, pepper, potatoes, Worcestershire sauce, green pepper, cabbage, celery and bacon.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 20 minutes, or until tender.

title: lemon lime pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Dissolve lime gelatin in boiling water and add frozen lemonade and cold water. Chill until almost set.
Chill milk, bowl and beaters for several hours before whipping milk.
Fold whipped milk into partially set gelatin, add lemon juice, put in crumb lined pan and chill until set.
Serve with sugar-free low-fat topping.
Yield:
6 servings; 1/6 pie:
carbohydrate 35 g, protein 4 g, fat 6 g, calories 210. One serving = 2 bread starch exchange, 1 fat exchange 1/2 fruit exchange.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and pour over oyster crackers. Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Cook on high for 2 minutes, until sugar is dissolved.
Stir using candy making temperature probe.
Set on 4 and cook to soft ball (234° to 240°).
Transfer to mixer bowl; add vanilla.
Beat with dough hook until it snaps.
If you do not have a dough hook, beat with a spoon until it snaps.
Spoon on a buttered aluminum foil.

title: chocolate town chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add egg and beat well.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: feather rolls
directions: Combine the yeast, warm water and sugar; dissolve.
Combine the scalded milk, sugar, butter and salt; cool to lukewarm. Combine yeast mixture and milk mixture.
Add in eggs.
Mix in flour.
Dough should be slightly sticky.
Put oil in large bowl and spread over sides.
Place dough in bowl; turn over to coat all sides.
Let raise until double in size.
Shape into rolls and let raise.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy cheesy carrots(microwave)
directions: Combine carrots and water in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until crispy tender.
Add green peppers and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add cheese and cook 1 minute to melt cheese.
Let stand, covered just a few minutes before serving.

title: all star white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water. Warm milk, 1 cup water and butter together.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and salt; mix well.
Add yeast to cooled milk mixture.
Add flour slowly, stirring constantly.
Knead dough for 10 minutes; set aside in a greased bowl in warm place, turning dough once so that all sides are greased.
Cover with damp cloth.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours or until double.
Punch down, knead several minutes.
Shape into 3 loaves and place in greased pans.
Allow to rise until double. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned custard pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pan with plain pastry, brush with slightly beaten
egg whites (or 1 teaspoon melted butter) and set in refrigerator
to
chill
thoroughly.
Beat eggs slightly; then beat in sugar, nutmeg and milk.
Pour into chilled pastry pan. Bake at
for
minutes,
then reduce heat to 350° and finish baking.

title: frypan chocolate balls
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips at 190° in the frypan for 5 minutes.
Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate at least 15 minutes before serving or until firm.
Keep refrigerated.

title: banana freeze(diabetic)
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Divide mixture evenly into 6 paper cups; freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 5 to 6 minutes.
Peel paper cup as freeze is being eaten!
Yields 6 cups.

title: schmierkucken
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and butter.
Cool.
Measure water and add yeast.
Stir into milk mixture.
Add egg and half of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for 3 hours. May be left in fridge for 3 days. Makes 4 coffee cakes. Roll out like pie crust, less than 1/2-inch thick. Put in a greased pan and add filling.

title: coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together sugar and margarine. Mix eggs, buttermilk, flour, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells and bake 30 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 2 pies.

title: ruth's quiche lorraine
directions: Cook bacon crisp and crumble.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion on pastry.
Blend remaining ingredients with rotary beater and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 300° and bake for 30 minutes.
Insert knife; when it comes out clean, it is done.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together until sugar melts.
Cool, then add bananas, pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice. Freeze until ready to serve.

title: chocolate pecan fudge pie(no crust)
directions: Melt together margarine and chocolate.
Add sugar and eggs; mix in flour and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: breakfast taco
directions: Spray skillet with vegetable oil.
Dice potatoes and bacon. Scramble eggs in small bowl.
Cook diced bacon in skillet.
Add potatoes.
Cover with lid for about 3 minutes until cooked, then add eggs in and cook until done.
Warm tortilla and add 3 tablespoons cooked eggs, bacon and potatoes into tortilla and top with cheese; enjoy.

title: dry ramen noodles
directions: Remove Ramen noodles seasoning packets and keep 1 packet for later use.
Bring water to a boil and add noodles.
Boil for 2 minutes; rinse and drain.
In a large skillet, heat sesame oil over medium heat.
Add carrot, broccoli and meat.
Saute for 5 minutes. Gently stir in drained noodles, one packet Ramen noodle seasoning, soy sauce, pepper and green onions.
Saute a few minutes longer. Serve immediately.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Prepare pudding as instructed on box.
Slice Twinkies and layer in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Slice bananas and place in juice.
Layer pineapple over Twinkies.
Drain bananas and layer over pineapple.
Layer pudding, then Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts on top of cake. Chill and serve.

title: spinach and three onion salad
directions: Combine chives, shallot, red onion, parsley and Bleu cheese in salad bowl; toss gently.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix oleo, shortening, Coke and marshmallows and melt on low heat. Set aside to cool. Mix remaining ingredients. Combine and mix well. Add marshmallow mixture. Mix well. Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Sift the flour before measuring.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together into a mixing bowl.
Cut the shortening into the flour mixture with a pastry blender, two knives or a fork, until it is separated into small pieces giving the appearance of coarse meal.
Add the milk gradually.
At each addition, place the milk on an undampened portion of the fat-flour mixture.
Stir until the mixture forms a ball and follows the fork around the bowl.
Dust the board and your hands with flour, using just enough to keep the dough from sticking.
Knead the dough lightly, about 16 strokes.
With your hand or a rolling pin, pat or roll the dough to 1/2 inch thickness. Use light strokes.
Cut the dough with a cutter, dipped in flour.
Cut straight down without twisting the cutter. Lift the biscuits carefully from the board to the ungreased baking sheet with a spatula.
If you want crusty biscuits, place them an inch apart.
Place them with the sides touching if you want soft biscuits.
Bake in a hot oven, 450°, for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve at once.
Yields 12 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: abby's pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked shell.
Sprinkle over top 1 heaping cup of pecans.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: zucchini casserole(start this dish up to 4 hours ahead!)
directions: In a bowl, mix zucchini with salt; let stand 15 minutes. Drain and squeeze out as much liquid as possible.
Combine zucchini, eggs, flour, 1/2 cup cheese and herbs.
Spread evenly in a shallow greased 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° until set in center when touched, about 15 minutes.
Use or let stand up to 4 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, mix the hash browns, sour cream, soup and cheese.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Crush the cornflakes and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: amaretto mousse cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs with butter.
Press into bottom and up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan; chill.

title: sesame seed toffee
directions: Spread sesame seed on large baking sheet; toast in 350° oven until lightly golden, about 10 minutes, stirring often.
In 3-quart saucepan, melt butter or margarine; stir in corn syrup and sugar.
Cook and stir over high heat until candy thermometer reaches soft crack stage (290°).
Remove from heat and stir in sesame seed, vanilla and salt.
Immediately pour onto two buttered 15 x 10 x 1 1/2-inch jelly roll pans; spread out thinly.
Cool. Break into bite-size pieces.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: fudge cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: oyaku-dumbou(serves 4)
directions: Cut up chicken.
Cut up scallions, 1-inch pieces.
Chop onion in medium pieces.
Preheat electric skillet (320° to 340°).
Use 2 to 4 tablespoons of oil for frying.
Fry chicken first, then onions, then mushrooms.
Add soy sauce and broth.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Beat eggs.
Right before you are ready to serve, put eggs in.
Turn up heat a little and turn over eggs and chicken until set but not dry.
Serve over rice.

title: tandoori chicken
directions: Skin the chicken.
Make deep cuts in the meat with the point of the knife.
Sprinkle with salt and rub with vinegar.
Allow to stand 15 minutes.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shell, then bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: don's favorite dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts together and press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or almost brown.

title: baked swiss steak
directions: Roll steak in flour.
Brown in small amount of fat.
Put in baking pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, covered, for 2 to 2 1/2 hours in 325° oven.

title: boatshed chili
directions: In large stock pot, cook ground beef, strain fat. Set aside ground beef. In same pot saute vegetables in olive oil until soft. Add ground beef and rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered for about 2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: corn bake
directions: Melt butter. Stir in bread crumbs and 1/4 cup cheese.

In baking dish, combine corn, milk, egg, onion, salt and remaining cheese. Cook in microwave for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with crumb mixture and cook for 1 more minute. Brown under the broiler. Makes 6 servings.

title: heavenly or angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift dry ingredients into large bowl; cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk, then yeast.
Stir until thoroughly moistened.
Turn onto floured surface and knead.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thick; cut with 2-inch cutter.
Place on ungreased sheet; brush with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 60 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Clean and cut up chicken; place in kettle and partly cover with water.
Add onion, salt and pepper and cook until tender. Mix flour, baking powder, salt, a little minced parsley and milk to thick batter.
Drop from spoon into slowly boiling broth. Cover tightly and let simmer 20 minutes before lifting cover.

title: veli good beans
directions: When the barbecue is going, tuck ears of sweet corn on the grill.

title: oat pancakes
directions: Combine oats, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Pour into well. Stir just until moistened.

title: don's dip
directions: To increase, add everything double, but Salsa Brava add to taste.

title: good cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl until gooey.
Press into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes. Cool for 5 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: gumbo
directions: In large stock pot heat oil.
Add flour.
Cook and stir on med. heat until mixture is the color of peanut butter and has a nutty aroma.
Be sure to stir constantly or it will burn.
Add onion, celery, green pepper, and garlic and saute 1-2 minutes. Slowly add chicken stock or water.
Stir until combined.
Add okra and seasonings.
Simmer on low 1 - 1 1/2 hours.
Add meat the last 30 minutes.
Serve in a bowl over rice.
Top with tabasco or other hot sauce if desired.
Serves 4-5.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Layer a casserole dish with the tortillas.
Mix pizza sauce and ground beef together.
Then place in dish.
Top with grated cheese. Cook at 375 until cheese in melted.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: strawberry dream cake
directions: Place layer of cake in the bottom of a large glass bowl.
Pour in vanilla pudding, enough to almost cover.
Add strawberries and few spoons of jam.
Repeat two times.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with almonds.
Prepare a few hours before serving or overnight.
Keep refrigerated.
Good light summer dessert!

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in pineapple over low heat.
Remove from heat and fold in softened cream cheese, sugar and baby food.
Place in refrigerator until mixture begins to thicken.
