Fold in Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts and return to the refrigerator.

title: one, two, three, four cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add flour, salt and baking powder alternately with milk.
Then add vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or two 8-inch layer pans for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together; pat down in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: press 'n bake cream cheese crust
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter, then flour, blending well. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Press into ungreased 9-inch pie pan.

title: very simple christmas candy
directions: Melt chocolate and add the rest of the ingredients.
Break small pretzels into short links and add as much as you like.
Drop by spoon on waxed paper.
Brown or white chocolate can be used. Directions for melting may be found on package.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, egg, sugar, margarine, shortening, molasses and milk together.
Add oatmeal to batter.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until edges are brown.

title: flora's blueberry open-faced pie
directions: Place uncooked blueberries in pie crust.
Mix sugar and flour well.
Add water to sugar and flour mixture.
Mix to a thin paste. Pour over berries.
Bake in 350° oven until crust is brown and filling is thickened.

title: ground beef, rice and corn casserole
directions: In a roaster, break meat into very fine pieces and put over the rice, which was sprinkled over the bottom of roaster. Pour corn with juice over that. You can put green pepper strips on top. Put some tomato sauce on top (if prefer). Bake, covered, at 300° for a good hour. Kids love it.

title: weight watcher's peanut butter fluffs
directions: Line a muffin pan (12) with 2 1/2-inch paper muffin cups.
In a small bowl, combine the graham cracker crumbs and margarine. Press 1 tablespoon crumb mixture in each liner.
Top each with 2 teaspoons whipped topping.
Set aside.
In a large bowl with mixer on low, cream peanut butter and milk.
Add pudding mix and beat 1 minute or until well mixed.
Fold in the remaining whipped topping.
Divide the mixture evenly between the muffin cups and top each with dollop of strawberry jam.
Freeze for several hours or overnight.

title: macaroni and chicken supreme casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in greased covered casserole dish.
Make head and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 tablespoons of ice water.
Add 1 cup boiling water and let cool.
Combine pineapple and juice, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Add to gelatin mixture and let partially congeal in refrigerator.
Fold in 2 envelopes of the Dream Whip, prepared according to package directions.
Rub brown off cake, break cake in bite-size pieces.
Line a deep 12-inch round dish with a layer of cake.
Alternate congealed mixture with layers of the cake pieces (about 2 cake layers).
End with congealed mixture on top.

title: granny's old fashioned brownies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs; mix well. Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir until blended.
Bake at 350° for 22 to 25 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain 2 cans of green beans.
Put in a casserole dish.
Mix with 2 cans of mushroom soup and 3/4 can of dry onions.
Put remaining onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rugala
directions: Mix margarine and cream cheese and slowly add the flour and vanilla.
Knead dough on floured surface and refrigerate till cool.
Roll out on slightly floured surface till flat.

title: european coffee cake
directions: Soften yeast in warm water; set aside. Combine scalded milk, sugar, shortening, salt and almond extract. Blend in 1 egg and softened yeast. Gradually add flour to make a soft dough. Beat well. Cover; let rise in warm place until light and doubled, about 1 1/2 hours. Pat out in well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Spread with cherry pie filling. Combine sour cream, egg, sugar, almond flavoring and salt. Drizzle over cherries. Let rise in warm place until light. Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar until particles are size of peas. Sprinkle over coffee cake. Bake in 350° oven for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cheese, milk and sugar.
Add vanilla and peanut butter. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: batter for fish
directions: Sift dry ingredients, add egg yolk and water; fold in beaten egg white.
Dip fish in batter and fry to golden brown.

title: shrimp with noodles
directions: Heat soup and water until soup is thawed. Blend in sour cream. Add shrimp and paprika. Heat a few minutes; stir often. Serve over noodles.

title: snow soup
directions: Brown ground beef or ground turkey in a 5-quart Dutch oven or heavy pot.
Skim off all fat.
Slice and add carrots, celery and onion.
Add tomatoes, barley, bouillon cubes, freshly ground pepper, parsley and 6 cups of water.
Simmer 1 hour or until barley is fully cooked.
Serve with hot bread or rolls, a glass of milk and fresh fruit.

title: portugese bean soup
directions: Wash beans; add water. Bring to boil, then reduce heat.

Cook gently for 1 hour. Saute onions, garlic and fat until golden. Add with remaining ingredients; cover and continue to simmer for 1 hour or longer. Do not add salt to initial cooking water, since it will tend to make the beans tough.

title: chicken linguine
directions: Mix cheese, milk, wine, cornstarch, salt, thyme, cervil and pepper in small bowl and set aside.
Stir-fry in small amount of oil the onion, celery and bell pepper about 1 minute.
Add mushrooms and cook one more minute.
Set aside.
Cook chicken slices until no more pink shows.
Put vegetables back into wok and heat them through.
Add cheese/milk mixture and cook until thick and hot.
Serve over hot, drained linguine.

title: orange salad
directions: Prepare jello according to directions.
Cool, then add the cottage cheese and mix.
Add the orange slices; fold in the Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: grandma's spoon bread
directions: Add the corn meal gradually to the milk, stirring constantly to prevent lumping.
Cook over moderate heat for at least 15 minutes until the mixture thickens.
Add butter, sugar and salt; set aside for a few moments while you beat the egg yolks.
Spoon and stir the yolks into corn meal mixture; set aside while you beat the egg whites stiffly.
Fold them into the corn meal mixture, stirring well, but slowly.
Pour into a greased casserole or cast-iron skillet.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve hot from the baking container with milk, apple butter, ham and beans!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add cooked noodles.
Mix tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Set aside 1/4 cup of sauce mix.
Add remaining sauce to meat mixture.
Layer meat and cheese twice. Put set aside sauce on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat english muffins
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put on untoasted English muffins. Cut into quarters.
(They can be frozen and stored in plastic bag in freezer.)
Place on a baking sheet and broil for about 6 minutes or until brown on top.
(They can be cooked in a toaster-oven-broiler.)

title: orange jello cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour pan.
Combine cake mix and Jell-O in bowl.
Add oil and water.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs.
Pour in a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake for 1 hour. Poke holes with fork and pour frosting on top.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: In medium sauce pan, mix gelatin, spices and salt.
Blend in eggs beaten with the milk.
Let stand one minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Blend in pumpkin and mix well.
Turn into pie crust and chill 1 hour.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Add water and 1 cup of the berries.
Cook until thick, stirring continually.
Add butter, rest of berries and cinnamon.
Cool mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
When served, top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: white bread
directions: Sprinkle sugar and yeast on warm water.
Set aside to work.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain.
Add soups, picante sauce and milk together and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Pour half of meat mixture into baking dish; top with crunched up Doritos and grated Mozzarella and Cheddar cheeses.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg and press into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tangy chicken and pineapple
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
In saucepan, mix together pineapple juice, lime juice, soy sauce and ginger.
Place cornstarch in measuring cup or small bowl; add 3 tablespoons of the juice mixture and stir until smooth.
Over high temperature, place saucepan containing juice mixture and bring to a boil.
Stir in cornstarch mixture; stir until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat and dip each pineapple slice into the mixture.
Place pineapple in bowl for later use.
Dip chicken halves into sauce and place on grill or pan.
Put remaining sauce in pot and bring to boil.
Grill chicken; baste with the sauce every 10 minutes. Grill pineapple slices 1 minute on each side.
Place a pineapple slice on top of each chicken half.
Top each piece with a teaspoon of sauce.
Makes 10 servings; 245 calories a serving.

title: cranberry-raspberry mold
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin in bowl.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Refrigerate until very thick, but not set.
Beat in sour cream and cranberry sauce with hand beater.
Pour into five cup mold.
Refrigerate until firm; unmold.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in a saucepan and cook gently, stirring constantly.
Good over ice cream, etc.
Should it get lumpy, strain.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar,
salt
and	vanilla in bowl and mix well with mixer.
Pour	into
can,
add condensed milk and stir well.	Add dairy milk	to
full
line	and stir.
Use crushed ice and put ice cream salt on the ice as you fill your container. Makes 4 quarts.

title: mock boursin au poivre
directions: Blend cream cheese with garlic, caraway, basil, dill weed and chives.
Pat into flat round shape.
Roll on all sides with lemon pepper.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: best sauerkraut
directions: Do not use plastic.
Use a 5-gallon crock or glass jar.
Chop cabbage, onion and peppers.
(Wear gloves to protect hands from peppers.)
Place cabbage, onion and peppers in crock.
Repeat the chopped vegetables and put in crock, until crock is full.
In a gallon glass jar, mix vinegar and salt.
Fill jar with water. Pour over cabbage.
Make this solution and pour over cabbage until it is completely covered.
Weight the cabbage down with a plate (not plastic).
Set a quart jar of water on top of plate; cover with a clean cloth.
Let stand 7 to 10 days, or until it stops working.
Skim scum off as needed.
Pack into clean canning jars. Seal; cook for 10 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes about 15 to 17 pints.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add Ragu. While this is simmering, put a layer of Frito-Lay corn chips in a pan and heat in oven until warm (this gives chips a totally different flavor). Individuals may put mixture in a dish; top with cheese, tomato and lettuce. Use Scoops to eat.

title: carrot cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in egg.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Press mixture into desired cookie shapes and place on large, flat cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tossed salad
directions: Break equal parts of the lettuce into bite size pieces.
Slice mushrooms.
Slice onion into rings.
Sprinkle freely with Parmesan cheese.
Add croutons and toss together.
Pour dressing over just before serving.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes on sheet and then remove to foil on countertop.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs and mix well.
Add strawberries and nuts.
Mix and bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool completely before wrapping in foil for freezing.

title: holiday aroma
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer in crock-pot during the holidays.
A lovely aroma; add water as necessary.

title: stuffed flounder rolls(makes 4 servings)
directions: In bowl, mix rice, scallions, 3 tablespoons steak sauce and egg.
Spoon mixture on fillets; roll up.
Arrange in 2-quart baking dish.
In small bowl, combine wine, margarine and remaining steak sauce; pour over fish fillets.

title: over-stuffed baked potatoes(makes 2 servings)
directions: Bake potatoes in preheated hot oven (425°) for 50 minutes or until fork-tender.
Meanwhile, saute squash, mushrooms and onion in margarine in saucepan, 5 minutes or until fork-tender.
Scoop out insides of potatoes.
Whip with skim milk in bowl.
Stir in cheese. Refill shells and place on serving plates.
Mound vegetables over potatoes.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: dump cake pudding
directions: Pour pineapple and liquid into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread cake mix over pineapple. Dot with margarine slices and sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: congealed salad(lo-cal)
directions: Heat diet drink to boiling.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved. Chill until congealed.
Stir in cottage cheese and pineapple. Chill until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: After everything is cooked, put in casserole dish and add Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
Mix well and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dream pie
directions: Mix until thick with mixer the Dream Whip mix, cold milk and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well the cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Pour into 2 small graham cracker pie shells or 1 large shell.
Spread out and cover with pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: oriental cabbage
directions: Fry until done.
Add 3/4 cup of evaporated milk.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Rinse crawfish tails.
In a large skillet, saute in butter the onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic. Add crawfish tails and continue to saute until thoroughly heated. Add cream of mushroom soup and seasonings to taste.
Stir in rice.
Pour into large casserole and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake until bubbly and crumbs are lightly browned, approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Simmer zucchini until tender; drain about 10 minutes.
Saute 4 tablespoons butter, onions and carrots until tender.
Mix with zucchini, 1 1/2 cups stuffing and soup in casserole.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and 1 cup stuffing crumbs; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick frying-pan zucchini
directions: Place olive oil in heavy skillet.
Add zucchini and garlic salt to heated oil, then add the dry vermouth.
Put lid on pan and shake about 2 minutes.
Pour off excess liquid; shake another 1 minute.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients alternately with zucchini.
Stir in raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes; turn out onto wire racks to cool.
Freezes well.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: nut cake
directions: Mix margarine, eggs and sugar.
Combine with flour.
Mix in nuts.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or done.

title: deep dish peach pie
directions: Pour peaches (drained) into a 3-inch deep pan.
Mix milk, flour and sugar.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 375° until browned on top.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and press in wax paper-lined pan. Store in refrigerator.

title: italian bean and sausage stew
directions: Cut sausage into 3/4-inch pieces; remove casing.
Cook in large saucepan over medium-low heat until lightly browned.
Add onions and garlic; cook until sausage is no longer pink, about 3 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Add tomatoes, beans, sauce, basil and oregano.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add green pepper, zucchini and cornstarch mixture; continue cooking 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender and sauce is thickened. Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: granny's homemade apple butter
directions: First, core and slice apples, but do not peel.
Place on stove and add only enough water to cook apples until soft.
Then run apples through a food press and measure.
You need 16 cups of apple pulp.
Then combine all other ingredients with apple pulp. Place on stove and cook until mixture remains in a smooth mass when a little cooled.
This will require about 50 minutes boiling time.
Stir frequently to prevent burning.
When done, pour into sterilized pint size jars and seal while hot.
Makes around 9 jars.

title: apricot bars with glaze
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pat into a 9-inch square pan. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Take out of oven and spread with apricot preserves.
Mix the next 4 ingredients until crumbly; spread over preserves. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: date nut fingers
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; beat in sugar and vanilla.
Stir in the other ingredients.
Mix.
Spread in greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut into finger slices.
Roll pieces in powdered sugar if desired.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix peppers, onion, sugar and vinegar and bring to a rolling boil.
Add Certo and return to a rolling boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Skim off the foam and pour into jars and seal.

title: low calorie dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.
Stir well and serve over crisp salad greens.
Two tablespoons of dressing contains 25 calories.

title: cobbler crust
directions: Mix
flour
and
salt
in
mixing bowl; add shortening; blend well
until
coarse.
Add water; mix well.	Sprinkle on pastry sheet and roll thin.
Cut in strips and place on top of favorite filling.
Overlap
each strip.
When pie is covered, brush with melted butter
and	sprinkle
with	sugar.	Bake at 350° until brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add the eggs, soda and sour milk mixture and flour.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hash brown crunch
directions: Mix together and put in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Top with 1 teaspoon oleo and 2 cups crushed cornflakes or potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine first
7 ingredients;
shape into 24 meatballs. Brown meatballs
in oil in 4 quart Dutch oven.
Remove as they brown. Combine
soup
and broth in Dutch oven.
Add meatballs and vegetables.
Bring	to
boil.
Cover
and
simmer
for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Optional Cooking:
I fix in oven at 350° until vegetables are tender in roaster.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer on low to medium heat, stirring until sauce starts to thicken.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and pick off bone.
Put in casserole dish.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, soup, beans and Ro-Tel. Layer bottom of baking dish with half the chips; add half the mixture, then more chips, more mixture, then chips until all is used.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 25 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Spread a thin layer of sauce on crust. Beat eggs in container and add some salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Pour onto crust.
Spread the cheese on top of the eggs. Add sausage and bacon.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes.
Cut into 10 slices.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut juice and put in sugar and water. Bring to a boil. Pour over other ingredients.
Set overnight.
Serve.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix thoroughly.
Add Quaker oats.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: country pot roast
directions: Trim most of fat from roast. Boil until tender with chipped garlic.
Slice large onion over meat and cook until onion is well done.
Remove meat from broth.
Thicken broth with flour and water.
Return meat to gravy and cook until gravy is done.
(I add a teaspoon of sugar to my meat along with salt and pepper.) Good over rice or creamed potatoes.

title: six layer dinner
directions: In order given, layer ingredients in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Bake covered in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Saute stems in oil.
Remove from pan.
Cook sausage to crumbly stage, drain.
Add mushroom stems and rest of ingredients.
Stuff mushroom caps.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on cookie sheet.
Serve hot or freeze.

title: corn and sausage dish
directions: Brown sausage, celery and onion.
Mix rest of ingredients with 1/2 cup of cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix with 2 quarts of cold water.
Mix well and serve chilled.

title: basic white sauce
directions: Place butter in 4-cup glass measure and cook on High for 1 minute.
Stir flour into butter until smooth.
Whisk in milk, pepper and nutmeg, blending well.
Cook on High for 3 minutes, stirring once.
At pause, whisk until smooth.
Cook on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until thickened.
Serve with cooked broccoli or cauliflower.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening.
Stir in light brown sugar.
Cool slightly. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs to cooled sugar mixture, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Add flour mixture to egg and sugar mixture.
Add chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Blend well.
Spread in 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 3/4-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: double decadence chocolate chip brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add 1 cup chocolate chips, melted.
Mix well.
Add flour, oats, baking powder, remaining chocolate chips and nuts, mixing well.
Spread into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until brownies pull away from side of pan.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.
To melt chocolate chips, microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds until smooth.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix and bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed scallops
directions: Combine melted butter, bread crumbs and sherry.
In buttered casserole alternate layers/scallops with crumb mixture, ending with crumbs.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Pour evaporated milk over all and dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven for 25 minutes.
Serve on toast points.

title: cold fruit soup
directions: Combine fruit, water, sugar, salt and cinnamon in a saucepan. Bring to boil; cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Put in blender. Mix cornstarch with little water and stir into the fruit mixture. Cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Chill and garnish with sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix oats and buttermilk; let stand 5 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add sugar and egg whites.
Add oat mixture; stir just until blended.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, mix and bake cake according to package directions.
In a saucepan, bring crushed pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Pour mixture over hot cake.
Mix pudding according to directions of package.
Pour over cake; refrigerate until cool. Spread Cool Whip on cooled cake.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on top of cake.
Good for large group.

title: cocoa brownies supreme
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Add cocoa and mix thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in.
Add walnuts.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese add marshmallow cream.
Beat until smooth. Serve with fruit.

title: easy homemade soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat in 2-quart boiler.
Add vegetable soup and tomato juice.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Ready to eat!

title: chili-corn bread
directions: Combine the corn, sour cream, butter and eggs.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir the cornmeal, salt and baking powder together to blend.
Stir the dry ingredients into liquid ingredients, blending well.
Stir in the cheese and chiles.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: "musical meat loaf"
directions: Combine all ingredients by hand well. Shape into a loaf. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. Very important to sing or hum while preparing. Must play "Moon Light Sonata" while baking. Serve hot with vegetables or cold as sandwiches.

title: cake box cookies
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook onions and margarine until onions are transparent.
Mix other ingredients and place in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix stuffing with 2 tablespoons margarine and spread over casserole. Bake in oven at 300° until bubbly and brown.

title: potato candy
directions: Mash baked potatoes in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix until consistency is like dough.
Roll on wax paper.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll into log.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Slice.
Store in refrigerator.
Rolls may be frozen.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain excess fat.
Cook elbow macaroni according to package instructions and drain.
Combine beef mixture, macaroni, tomatoes, peas and seasoning in Dutch oven.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes to heat through.

title: honey-gingered pork tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloins in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Combine honey and next 9 ingredients, stirring well.
Pour over tenderloins.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 8 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove tenderloins from marinade, reserving marinade.
Grill tenderloins over medium hot coals 25 to 35 minutes, turning often and basting with reserved marinade.
Pork is done when meat thermometer inserted into thickest portion of meat.
Slice tenderloins.
Serve on a platter, garnish with parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add molasses and buttermilk; beat.
Add flour, cinnamon and nutmeg last.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with lemon sauce.
(See Lemon Sauce recipe.)

title: tuna ball
directions: Leave cream cheese out until it is room temperature. Beat until fluffy. Add all ingredients, except nuts. Combine and refrigerate for 1 hour. Make into ball and roll in nuts.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and pour into muffin tins and freeze until firm.
Mandarin oranges (drained) can be substituted for cherries and nuts.	Serves 12.

title: ground cherry preserve
directions: Cook all the ingredients until almost clear but still runny. Boil about 10 minutes. Crush or grind the mixture if desired. Preserves can be frozen or stored in refrigerator.

title: erlette's fruitcake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and spices.
Mix in fruit and nuts.
Pour into a greased tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Enjoy!

title: evan's frozen french fry casserole(kid recipe)
directions: Cook hamburger until done; drain.
Pout 1/2 of frozen French fries in baking dish.
Layer 1/2 of hamburger, pour half the corn and half of the soup on top.
Make another layer just like this and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: krazy chocolate cake
directions: Put sugar, flour, cocoa, soda and salt into about a 15-inch oblong pan (the one you are going to bake it in).
Do not grease the pan.
Mix vinegar, vanilla and oil and then add.
Then pour water over all and mix together until all of the lumps are out. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer (until done).
While still partly warm, put on this filling.

title: easy chicken breasts
directions: Moisten chicken breasts in the melted margarine.
Roll breasts in crouton crumbs.
Coat both sides.
Cook breasts, covered, with wax paper in the microwave.
Cook on high about 2 to 3 minutes per breast.
Be careful not to overcook.

title: ham-potato scallop
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole layer half of the ham, half of the onion and half of the potatoes.
Repeat layers.
Mix soup, milk and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for about 1 hour or until potatoes are almost tender.
Mix crumbs, parsley and margarine. Sprinkle atop casserole. Bake uncovered for 15 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken cheese puff ring
directions: Boil chicken.
Chop chicken and green onion into fine pieces. Combine all ingredients.
Unroll crescent dough; separate into triangles.
Arrange triangles in a circle on a round baking sheet with wide ends overlapping in center and points toward outside. (There should be a 5-inch diameter opening in center.)
Scoop chicken mixture evenly onto widest end of each triangle.
Bring points of triangles up over filling and tuck under wide ends of dough at center of ring.
(Filling will not be completely covered.)
Bake 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli and ham strata
directions: In a large bowl mix chopped ham, broccoli, onion and 2 cups Cheddar cheese. Butter a 3-quart baking dish.
Place trimmed bread on bottom of dish.
Spoon broccoli-ham mixture over bread.
Beat eggs with dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and milk; pour over broccoli mixture and sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Cheddar cheese. Let stand for 10 minutes before baking.
Place baking dish in pan of hot water and bake in a 375° oven for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Mix Cinnamon Crisp crumbs and butter.
Combine sliced apples, sugar and flour; place in an unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over top.
Add milk.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cindy's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat with a spoon.
Add pecans if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: aunt alice's holupki
directions: Cut core out of cabbage and steam until leaves soften.
Wash rice several times until water becomes clear.
Cover with water, heat to boiling.
Turn off and rinse in cold water.
Drain

title: 5 bean salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Pour over vegetables. Let set overnight.
Add garlic and basil to taste.

title: fresh fruit cobbler topping
directions: Mix together and crumble over fruit in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix into batter.
Cut onions in slices about 1/4-inch and let fat get hot.
Drop rings into hot grease and brown.

title: mustard steak
directions: For marinade, whisk together all ingredients, except meat. Place steak in a shallow dish and cover with marinade to coat thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 6 hours, turning occasionally.
Grill or broil, basting with marinade until desired doneness.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring cranberries, salt and 1 pint of water to a boil; add soda and cook 10 minutes.
Remove from fire and add sugar, jello, 2 cups of water and marshmallows; stir until dissolved.
Cool and add celery, apples and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: bugs on a log
directions: Cut off the ends of the celery sticks and carrot; wash real good.
Spread peanut butter in the center of the celery sticks. Place the raisins on top of the peanut butter.
Shred carrot and sprinkle on top of peanut butter and raisins.
Arrange on a plate and serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sirloin tips and gravy
directions: Brown steak in butter along with onion and green pepper, until meat is cooked through.
Remove from pan and drain excess fat.
In same pan, add gravy mix to water.
Mix well and simmer 5 minutes. Add meat mixture and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over rice and noodles.

title: creamy delight
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Beat with mixer until smooth and creamy. Gradually blend in confectioners sugar.
Blend in topping.
When filling is well blended, spoon into prepared graham cracker crust. Top with pie filling.
Chill.

title: carrot croquettes
directions: Mash or press carrots through coarse sieve.
Add salt, nutmeg, egg and butter and mix thoroughly.
Form into shapes, resembling carrots.
Roll in bread crumbs and chill for several hours.
Fry in hot, deep fat at 380° until browned.
Drain on absorbent paper. Tuck sprig of parsley on top and serve at once.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato cake with fresh coconut filling
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt.
In a large bowl with electric mixer, beat sugar and oil for 2 minutes.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in dry ingredients, hot water, sweet potatoes and walnuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff, fold into batter.
Pour into 3 well-greased and floured 8-inch round pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until cake springs back to touch.
Cool on a wire rack for 10 minutes.
Turn out of cake pans and cool completely.

title: stuffed steaks
directions: You will need toothpicks to secure openings on steaks.

title: low-fat pie crust
directions: Mix and pat into pan to form crust.
Top crust must be worked on waxed paper and gently eased off onto pie.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain any grease. Cook onions and peppers in skillet.
In a large pot, mix soup, tomato sauce, cheese, dried taco mix, evaporated milk and crushed chips.
Mix well; add meat, onions and peppers.
Mix well.
Put in a large ungreased dish (10 x 13-inch).
Top with any leftover chips to decorate top or leave plain.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Feeds 6 hungry people.

title: oatmeal bread(allergy-free recipe)
directions: Mix rolled oats and hot water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in honey, salt and bananas.
Add flour, soda and powder and stir until all ingredients are well mixed.
Turn into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and let stand 20 minutes in warm place.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cajun chicken
directions: In small frying pan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Remove from heat and stir in cayenne, garlic salt, oregano and paprika. In shallow dish place bread crumbs.
Dip chicken, one piece at a time, first in margarine then in bread crumbs, turning to coat on all sides.
On a lightly greased baking sheet place chicken in a single layer.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes or until brown and crisp and fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Serve with rice and sauteed sweet peppers.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix together scalded milk, sugar, shortening and salt; let cool.
Add to milk mixture 1 1/2 cups flour and egg; beat well.
Add softened yeast mixture and 1 1/2 cups flour to make soft dough.
Cover and let rise 10 minutes. Knead last cup of flour in for 5 minutes.
Put in a greased bowl (covered) and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and fold from side to side.
Let rise a second time until doubled.
Make into a ball.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Pat out to remove air.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except buttered bread crumbs.
Place in a greased casserole dish; top with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lemon jello fruit salad
directions: Prepare the Jell-O.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar, drained pineapple, apples and bananas.
Pour into oiled Pyrex dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Let cool and crumble in chunks.
Mix powdered sugar, egg yolks and oleo. Add Cool Whip. Crumble the Butterfingers.
(If you freeze these before, they will crumble finer.)
Layer cake crumbs, Cool Whip mixture, then Butterfinger crumbs.

title: public school butter cookies
directions: Mix and bake in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: In two different bowls, mix strawberry jello with one cup hot water for each.
Add to each 1 package of frozen strawberries and 1/2 large can crushed pineapple.
Jell one bowl in refrigerator until set.
Leave other bowl out so it will not set.
Spread sour cream over jelled part, then carefully spoon the unjelled mixture over this.
Return to refrigerator until all is set.

title: golden bread pudding
directions: Mix fruit cocktail and brandy in covered container at least 24 hours before you plan to make bread pudding.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla until light.
Add milk and blend well.
Add blended ingredients to creamed mixture. Spread half of batter in a 9-inch square pan.
Spoon berries over batter.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of cinnamon-sugar mixture. Spread remaining batter over blueberries.
Sprinkle remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture on top of batter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh cranberry punch
directions: Combine berries, water, cloves and cinnamon in large kettle. Bring to boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 12 to 15 minutes. Strain cooked juice through fine sieve or cheesecloth, squeezing gently.
Add orange and lemon juices to cranberry juice; add sugar and stir until sugar dissolves.
Serve piping hot.
Yields 25 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: paul newman cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
With the end of the handle of a wooden spoon, poke holes in cake.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over, then pour ice cream topping over it.
Spread with whipped topping.
Crush candy bars before unwrapping, then unwrap and sprinkle on top of whipped topping.

title: grandma's old-fashioned butter roll
directions: Note:
You
may
use
Bisquick dough.
Oleo may be used instead of butter, but it will not be as good.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and cook rice.
(You can cook rice ahead of time.)
Saute onions, celery, and bell pepper in margarine.
Mix all ingredients including soups and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (25-30 minutes).

title: tuna fish sauce
directions: Bring all the ingredients to a boil, stirring very often. Lower heat to simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve over very, very thin pasta, such as capellini.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, carrots, green pepper and onion together in a large cooking pan.
Cover with water and cook until vegetables are tender, about 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes, until a little thick.
Turn stove off and add butter, milk and salt and pepper.

title: chocolate-almond cream pie
directions: Break up Hershey almond bar in large bowl.
Place in microwave for 90 seconds until soft.
Blend the two whipped toppings together with the melted chocolate.
Pour equal parts into crusts. Put in freezer until ready to eat.
Roasted pecans may be added if desired.

title: crock-pot pork barbecue
directions: Cook pork roast in a crock-pot overnight or until fall-apart tender.
Add about 1/4 cup water to the pot when cooking.
Remove roast from pot.
Cool and chop into small pieces.
Remove as much fat as possible.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In large bowl, mix soup, tomatoes and milk together.
Stir in chicken.
In large casserole dish or pan, cover bottom with chips. Pour half of mixture on top and then repeat process. Top with any kind of shredded cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Combine cake
mix
and	nuts
in
a large bowl.
Cut in butter and stir in evaporated milk.
Spread half the batter in a greased 13	x
x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally,
until
caramels are melted.	Sprinkle chocolate chips
evenly
over
baked	layer.	Drizzle caramel syrup
over chocolate
chips,
carefully
spreading
to cover chocolate layer.
Drop
remaining chocolate batter by heaping teaspoonfuls over
caramel layer.
Return to oven and bake 20 to
minutes. Top
layer	will
be
soft.
Cool completely before cutting. Makes 48 brownies.

title: christmas fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water in separate bowls. Add juice from cocktail, 1/2 to each bowl.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) cake pans.
When set, cut in small cubes.
Combine with cocktail and bananas (cut small).
Chill and serve.
May add nuts, if desired.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil
and sugar;
blend well.	Add flour, salt and soda; mix
well.
Add
vanilla,
chopped
apples and nuts. Pour into a greased and floured 8 or 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour
until
done.
While
cake
is
hot,
pour hot topping over it in the pan or serve plain.

title: date swirl cookies
directions: Cook dates, salt, sugar and water until thick.
Remove from fire, add lemon juice and nuts, cool.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add flour sifted with soda.
Chill in refrigerator for half hour.
Divide in three parts, roll each part into a rectangle about 1/4 inch thick.
Spread thin layer of cooled date mixture on dough.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill or freeze overnight or until firm enough to slice.
Bake in oven at 350°.
Makes 150 cookies.

title: pumpkin brownies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, margarine and pumpkin together.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Stir.
Add nuts.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook, cook, peel and dice potatoes. Fry bacon.	Combine potatoes, cheese, ham, onion, green peppers, mayonnaise, salt, garlic
salt and hot peppers in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle on top bacon and olives.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour, cocoa, baking soda, and salt.
In separate bowl stir together buttermilk and vanilla. Beat together butter and brown sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixture at medium-high speed about 3 minutes (5 minutes with a hand held).
Add egg, beating until combined well.
Reduce speed to low and alternately mix in flour mixture and buttermilk in batches, beginning and ending with flour.
Spoon 1/4 c. mounds of batter about 2 inches apart onto 2 buttered baking sheets.
Bake until cake springs back when touched, 12-14 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Cook chocolate cake mix according to directions.
Prick cake while hot and pour Kahlua over it.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, combine milk and chocolate pudding mix at low speed on electric mixer.
Fold in 3 cups Cool Whip.
Crumble 1/2 of cake into very large glass bowl.
Then layer on it the mousse mixture, a carton of Cool Whip and the Skor pieces.
Repeat layers the second time.

title: shirley's green beans
directions: Chop onion and cut bacon up into small pieces.
Fry together in a skillet.
When bacon gets brown, pour green beans into skillet and simmer for a few minutes.

title: peanut butter refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix these 3 ingredients together and form into a log.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into slices and eat.

title: cold eggnog
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and process until smooth.
Drink right away.
Makes 1 quart.

title: summer sausage
directions: Combine and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate; stir once a day for 3 days.
Separate into 3 balls.
Shape each into a roll.
Bake on broiler pan at 150° for 9 hours.
Turn occasionally.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing as package directs.
Cool.
Cook broccoli as package directs.
Cool.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer stuffing (on bottom), then broccoli and then chicken.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: On a glass plate, spread cream cheese on surface. Layer crab and then the cocktail sauce on top of the cream cheese. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: pancit gisado kanton or canton
directions: Note:
This kind of noodles can be found at any Filipino or Chinese store.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Place cloves and cinnamon (broken to fit) in tea ball and hang to fit in a Mr. Coffee coffee pot.
Secure tea bags with lid to fit as well.
Pour water in top of coffee maker and turn on machine.
While hot water is covering tea bags and spices, heat the remaining ingredients in a saucepan, stirring to dissolve sugar.
When tea has brewed, remove tea bags and spices and add juice and sugar mixture.

title: freckle face pancakes
directions: Mix as directed. Drizzle a small amount of batter from a teaspoon onto hot griddle to make funny eyes, nose and mouth. When they puff up, pour about 1/4 cup batter over them.
Turn when bubbles appear.
Bake other side until golden brown.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad(makes 6 servings)
directions: In a bowl, combine broccoli, cauliflower, onion, bacon bits and Cheddar cheese. In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sweetener and vinegar. Pour mayonnaise mixture over vegetable mixture. Mix well to combine. Cover and refrigerate at least 1/2 hour. Gently stir again just before serving. Serving Size: 1 cup.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake just till a silver knife inserted 1 inch from side of filling comes out clean.
Bake at 425° (hot oven) 45 to 55 minutes.

title: texas cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour and salt. Bring margarine, cocoa and water to boil. Beat eggs and sour cream.
Add vinegar and soda to the cocoa mixture.
Add flour mixture and beat. Bake in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: polish coffee cake (mixer)(servings: 12)
directions: Add 1/4 teaspoon of sugar and dry yeast to the 1/4 cup of warm water.
Allow yeast to proof.
Scald half and half, remove from heat and add butter.
Allow this to cool as the butter melts.
Mix next four ingredients in a mixing bowl until well blended.
Add 3 cups of flour, one at a time, into blended mixture, mixing well. Add half and half and butter, yeast and raisins.
Mix well.
Let raise until double in size (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: salsa
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 30 minutes. After it boils, mix 4 tablespoons cornstarch to 1/2 cup cold water. Drain 2 cups juice from pot and let cool. Mix cornstarch with ingredients in pot. Cook 30 to 45 minutes. Pour into jars, seal and process.

title: cajun cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. While cake is baking, mix topping ingredients.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix eggs, pudding, butter and sugar in large bowl, then blend with mixer on medium speed.
Add flour and blend by hand until well mixed.
Then add drained blueberries and mix.

title: spanish corn
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender but not browned.
Add corn and tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Season to taste with salt.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: punch for children
directions: Mix and add ice.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Follow recipe on box.
Substitute Egg Beaters for egg and applesauce for oil.
Bake as directed on box.
Cut when cool. Eat!

title: ratatouille
directions: Dice eggplants into cubes.
In a large size pot, fry in oil until the eggplant turns a golden brown color.
Cut red pepper and onions into cubes.
Add to cooked eggplants and stir vegetables. Wash zucchini and cut in circles.
Add to pot.
Add salt and pepper.
Once vegetables have cooked sufficiently, add minced garlic and fresh basil.
Pour in can of stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add a dash of sugar.
Turn heat down and let vegetables simmer for approximately 1/2 hour.
This dish tastes best when the vegetables have been allowed to stew for a couple of days in the tomato juice.
It is delicious eaten hot or cold.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to directions on box. Spread a spoonful of stuffing onto each cutlet and roll it, securing the cutlet with a toothpick.
Place the cutlets in a glass Pyrex baking dish in a single layer.
Prepare chicken gravy according to the package and pour the gravy on top of the roll-ups.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 5 people. Be sure to warn your guests about the toothpicks!

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread out crescent rolls on a greased 10 x 15 inch baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes; cool.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix; mix well.
Spread mixture over cool bread.
Refrigerate overnight; slice next day.
On each piece put a small, thin slice of red, yellow or green pepper. Also, you can put broccoli or mushrooms.
Great for parties! Makes 8 dozen.
tags: envelope Hidden Valley ranch dressing mix

title: easy mexican cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of a 9-inch pan.
Pour on chili with beans.
Top with grated cheese.
Heat until melted.

title: lemon breeze
directions: In small saucepan, combine lemon juice and gelatin.
Place over low heat and stir until gelatin is dissolved; cool.
In mixing bowl, beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff and glossy.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks in mixing bowl until thick and lemon-colored.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and gelatin mixture; gently fold in egg white mixture.
Spread evenly in graham cracker pie crust.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm. Cut into wedges.
Yields 8 servings.
(Graham cracker crumbs may be sprinkled on top of mixture as a garnish.)

title: formal yard birds
directions: Mix a day ahead.
With crescent rolls make 8 rectangles (close seams).
Put 1/2 cup chicken mixture in each rectangle, pick up each corner and twist together in center.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake 350° (20-25 minutes).

title: punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients except ginger ale.
Freeze.
Take out and thaw some and pour ginger ale over mixture.
Serves 100. Make cut in half to serve 50.

title: fried green beans
directions: Heat cooking oil.
Stir in rest of ingredients; cook over high heat, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes, or until tender.
Serve hot.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix everything, except milk, with electric mixer.
Pour milk into mixture until bowl is almost full.
Mix on lowest speed. Pour into freezer can and finish filling with milk.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray Pam in baking dish.
Spread pecans and coconut evenly on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions; pour over pecans and coconut.
Dissolve margarine with cream cheese and mix well.
Add sugar.
Refrigerate for one day before serving.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Add cut up shortening, not too fine.
Beat water, vinegar and egg; mix well in a jar.
Add to flour mixture; mix all together.
Makes enough pie crust mix for 3 pies.
This dough can be frozen, wrapped in wax paper.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes; reduce to 350° for about an hour.

title: granola
directions: Mix all the ingredients and store in refrigerator in jar or airtight bowl.

title: pig feet
directions: Get clean pig feet in meat department.
The whole ones are better (not split).
Put enough water to cover plus 2 inches.
Add bay leaves and some peppercorns.
Boil until tender and coming apart.
Eat while hot.

title: chicken and noodle soup
directions: Cook noodles in broth for 10 minutes.
Put all in cans.
Cook in pressure cooker 30 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: quick creamy beef
directions: Brown beef, add flour, slowly pour milk over.
Season to taste. Salt and pepper.
Add extras to toast (onion, mushrooms).

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Combine all salad ingredients in bowl (first five ingredients).
Mix dressing ingredients (last 7 ingredients) in blender.
Serves 8.

title: pearl's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix and add semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Drop by well rounded teaspoonful onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool on sheet on wire rack for 1 minute. Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: ruby apple salad
directions: In a bowl, stir jello in boiling water until dissolved. Chill until partially set. Fold in apples, celery and walnuts. Pour into a 1-quart serving bowl. Chill until firm, at least 4 hours. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water, salt and butter.
Cook slowly. Do not stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add peanuts.
Cook to hard crack stage, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add soda.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and melted butter.
Press into 8 x 12-inch pan. Beat until fluffy the eggs, confectioners sugar and butter (at room temperature).
Spread on crust.
Drain pineapple, spread on mixture, slice bananas and place over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Garnish with nuts and cherries, if desired. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix well first 2 ingredients; spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Blend and beat 5 minutes next 4 ingredients.
Spread this over crust.
Place 5 bananas over mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.

title: brownie mounds
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, syrup and eggs.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Stir into wet mixture.
Stir in melted chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix together and dip apple slices.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix 100% bran with boiling water and let stand. Cream the Crisco, sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour, soda
and salt together. Add All-Bran to the dry flour mixture. Add buttermilk to this dry mix.
Mix well.
Add 100% bran mixture, then add Crisco-sugar mix and stir well. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°. Keep batter in refrigerator.
Will keep several weeks.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: squash surprise
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and oregano.
Cook squash, cut in small pieces; drain.
Add to ground beef, then add spaghetti sauce. Cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir in shredded cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Serve with garlic bread or hot rolls.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Empty Bix-Mix into a large bowl.
Stir in milk or water and eggs; beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Add mustard and 1 cup of cheese; mix thoroughly.
Turn batter into prepared pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese; dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on rack before slicing.
Especially good sliced, buttered and toasted.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Dissolve jello in the 1/4 cup water; set aside.
Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add jello mixture.
Add blackberries.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350°
for about 40 minutes or until cake is done.

title: can-can chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except noodles, in a large skillet. Stir real well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir.
Serve with noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and baking powder; stir well.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in nuts and apples; mixture becomes thick.
Spoon into a buttered pie pan and spread evenly.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans creole
directions: Brown onions and pepper (green) in 3 tablespoons bacon fat. Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer for 2 hours, then add to beans in casserole.
Bake for 1 hour.
Very good.

title: english muffins
directions: To scalded milk, add sugar and fat.
Cool and add package of yeast, dissolved in lukewarm water, and beaten egg.
Blend in 3 cups sifted flour.
Knead with 1 cup flour.
Let double and knead. Rest for 1 minute.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut and let double.
Cook 8 to 12 plus minutes a side on medium heat on griddle or in frypan. May be frozen.

title: great peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients until blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese cakes
directions: In a bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream and sugar; mix well.
Shape cream cheese mixture into little cakes.
Dust with flour.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Saute cakes lightly on each side.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: Pour over ice ring in punch bowl.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: chocolate pie(makes 2)
directions: Put sugar in bowl and stir in cocoa and flour.
Mix well.
Add 3 eggs and 1 stick of melted margarine.
Add vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn bread mexicana
directions: Pour 1 tablespoon butter into medium skillet; add onion, green chiles and pimento.
Saute for 3 to 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add corn; cook for 1 minute.

title: that
directions: Brown meat lightly in a skillet.
Peel potatoes and onion, using 1 potato per person to be served and one extra.
Slice potatoes and onion as if you were making potato chips.
Top meat with potatoes and onion and top this with 1 can green beans, juice and all.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender.
Lastly, add seasoning or you may use gravy.
This provides a nutritious meal quick to make and the kids love it.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter	2
slices
bread; cut in 1/2-inch cubes and set aside. Cut
rest	of
bread.
Put 1/2 in bottom of dish.	Mix chicken, margarine,	salt,
