and pepper and spread over
bread. Put
rest
of
bread over chicken mixture.	Beat eggs and milk together and pour over casserole.
Chill.
Spoon soup
over casserole.	Sprinkle with buttered bread.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Add cheese the last few minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the
milk
and egg yolks together.
Then mix sugar, cornstarch and
salt
together
and
add
to
the milk and egg yolks.
Cook in microwave until thick.
Cool.
Then add peanut butter and vanilla.
Place in the baked pie crust and top with whipped cream.
Chill and top with chopped peanuts.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening with brown sugar.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet 3-inches apart.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and nuts; mix well.
Make into rolls; wrap and chill in refrigerator (or may be frozen). Slice and bake in oven at 350° until brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: carlton's hawaiian pizza
directions: If you cannot make flour tortilla, buy fat ones...like Mission brand...then you mix da ground pork, fresh ground ginger, teriyaki sauce, brown sugar and whatever else you like till you get one thick sauce.
Add a couple a eggs to make 'em stick.
Spread on tortilla.
T'row in some ham and pineapple.
Grate water chestnut or jicama and cheese on da top.
Bake in oven 20 or 30 or 40 minutes...till meat is done.

title: nutta la choy noodle clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch drops in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in noodles and nuts.
Dip out by teaspoons on wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: toni's taco pizza
directions: Prepare crust following package directions.
Spread tomato sauce evenly over crust; sprinkle oregano.
Mix taco seasoning according to package with hamburger.
Drain excess juice.
Spoon hamburger mixture evenly over crust.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts and crust is golden brown.
Add topping if desired and taco sauce.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix dressing and margarine together.
Press all but one cup of dressing mix into bottom of two-quart casserole dish.
Save one cup of mix for top of casserole.
Place chicken pieces on top of dressing mix.
Mix soup and one cup broth in separate bowl, then pour over chicken.
Place remaining dressing on top.
Cover and bake at 350° until soup bubbles, about 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain. Combine other ingredients and mix with macaroni.
Pour all ingredients into a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or less.
Do not overcook.

title: kay's lasagna
directions: Brown meat
and
add
sauce.
Simmer for a few minutes. Mix cottage cheese and egg.
Put thin layer of sauce on bottom of casserole
dish.
Layer
cooked
noodles,
sauce
on top of noodles, then
cheese and egg mixture, then Mozzarella cheese. Do this twice	and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or a little less. This recipe can be doubled.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix together salt, sugar, spice and vinegar; bring to a boil. Mix with the vegetables and cook for 5 minutes or until tomatoes turn light in color. Do not overcook. Pack lightly in jars.

title: busy mom's cake
directions: Use deep oblong pan.
Grease well.
Pour in pie filling, then pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts over this.
Shake cake mix on top.
Dot top with margarine.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate loves
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, melt butter or margarine and chocolate.
Add sugar and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved and thoroughly blended. Remove from heat and stir in nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Fold in oats.
Cool mixture to medium-warm.
Roll teaspoonfuls of mixture into balls.
Place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheets.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 6 dozen.
Contains about 30 calories each.

title: bay island vegetable soup
directions: Brown the beef and 1 cup onions.
Pour V-8 juice into large pan.
Add all the other ingredients and then add the browned beef mixture. Cook on medium until vegetables are tender.
Stir frequently.

title: marvelous marble fudge
directions: Line 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with plastic wrap.
In 2-quart saucepan, stir corn syrup and milk.
Add chocolate, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium-low heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Add sugar.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Spread in pan.
Drop peanut butter by teaspoonful on fudge.
Swirl with knife to marbleize.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Invert to cutting board.
Remove plastic wrap.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Crush vanilla wafers in a plastic bag with rolling pin.
Pour 1/2 of the crumbs into an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch square pan. Reserve the remaining crumbs for the top.
In a small bowl, whip butter, gradually adding sifted powdered sugar until light and fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Carefully drop the butter-sugar mixture on top of the crumbs by using a heaping teaspoonful of the mixture an inch or so apart.
Gently spread the mixture to form a layer on top of the crumbs.
Pour heavy cream into bowl; whip until thick, then fold in crushed pineapple and spread over the butter mixture.
Top with remaining wafer crumbs.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large baking dish.
Top with pats of butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble 1/4 pound crackers and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Melt margarine and pour over cracker crumbs. Place chicken over crumbs.
Mix soup, sour cream and chicken broth; pour over chicken.
Crumble remaining crackers and put on top of soup mixture.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue deer ham
directions: Put deer ham in roasting pan, salt and pepper.
Put potatoes (unpeeled), carrots and onions all around the ham and on top.
Pour barbecue sauce over the deer ham.
Fill with water until it covers the deer ham.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 450° for 4 hours.
Add water as needed during cooking process.

title: fresh fried corn
directions: With a sharp knife, remove corn from cob (outer 1/2 of kernel).
Take teaspoon and scrape down length of cob to extract rest of kernel and corn milk.
Salt and pepper and set aside.
Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Set aside.
Add corn to bacon fat in skillet and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add bacon and milk.
Cook 5 additional minutes.
Serve.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan and bring slowly to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil briskly 1 minute and cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: diet super soup
directions: Cook all together.
Long cooking improves flavor.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix the cheese, mayo, mustard and onion in a mixer; put half of the shredded beef in the mixture.
Chill.
Form in the remaining beef.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: sugar cinnamon toast
directions: Spread margarine on white bread as desired.
Sprinkle sugar over bread, then sprinkle cinnamon powder as desired to taste. Repeat for additional slices of toast, then place in toaster oven until margarine melted and bread toasted.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles until almost done and cool under cold running water.
Brown hamburger; drain and mix with spaghetti sauce.
Beat egg and mix with cottage cheese.
Slice Mozzarella cheese.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Serve over cream cheese with crackers.
Sauce will keep in refrigerator for 6 months.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: lemon-sweet cucumbers
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except cucumbers. Blend well.
Add cucumber slices.
Toss to coat.
Cover; refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
If desired, drain before serving.

title: homemade hominy
directions: Wash corn.
Put cold water in large cooker.
Add corn and let soak several hours, then add soda and place over medium heat. Bring to full rolling boil.
Reduce heat until just boiling and cook until corn is tender and skins or husks begin to loosen from the grain.
This may take all day.
After corn is tender and husks are loosened, remove from heat and drain.
Rinse and rub the grains through the hands gently to remove the skins.
Rinse and drain several times.
The hominy is now ready for use.
I use hickory cane corn.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a saucepan; cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens, about 12 minutes.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until frosting is cool and thick enough to spread.
Makes about 2 2/3 cups or enough to cover the tops of 3 (9-inch) layers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs until light and add. Press bananas and add lemon juice.
Blend with creamed mixture. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together, then combine.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased 1 pound loaf pan.
Bake at 375°
for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt butter and mix other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar and vanilla. When it forms stiff peaks, put on pie and brown in oven.

title: sizzling summer steak, barbecue style
directions: Pour teriyaki sauce over steak in shallow pan, marinate 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove steak from marinade, place on grill 4 to 5 inches from heat.
Cook to desired doneness.
Meanwhile, blend 1/2 cup marinade with remaining ingredients; thicken over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Serve with steak.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry banana sherbet
directions: Combine water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add orange juice and mashed bananas with crushed strawberries.
Cool and freeze.
When a soft mush consistency is achieved, remove from freezer and fold in beaten egg white (not too stiffly beaten). Continue freezing until firm enough to serve.
Makes 2 quarts. Keep covered when stored.

title: philadelphia cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage and cook. Heat 2 cups water to boiling with 1 teaspoon salt and add cabbage.
Cook about 10 minutes. Drain.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to instructions.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus squares
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and chopped pecans in mixer bowl; mix well.
Add 1 egg and egg white, beating just until moist.
Spread in lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cream confectioners sugar, cream cheese and vanilla in bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in remaining 2 eggs and egg yolk 1 at a time, scraping bowl frequently.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Cool in pan. Chill, covered with foil, overnight.
Yield:
32 servings.

title: quick chocolate cake(no egg)
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, salt, baking soda and baking powder into mixing bowl. Form a well in dry ingredients and add oil, water, vinegar and vanilla. Mix well and pour into a lightly greased and floured 9-inch cake pan. Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain and stir in other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove skin and bone and cut into bite size pieces. Boil noodles in chicken broth.
Add sour cream and soups to noodles when done.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour into casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until bubbly and bread crumbs are toasted.
Freezes well.

title: potato-tomato soup
directions: Fry and drain hamburger. Combine all in Dutch oven kettle and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour or until soup has thickened.

title: cinnamon butter
directions: Mix together with electric mixer.
Store in airtight container.
Keep in refrigerator; keeps indefinitely.

title: chocolate pie - no milk
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa; add enough water to make a paste. Heat 2 cups water, egg yolks, butter or margarine and salt until butter melts.
Add water mixture to cocoa paste and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue, sealing to the crust's edge.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and pour half of batter in 8-inch square pan (greased).
Cover with cheese.
Pour remaining batter over cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
(Use more cheese, if desired.)

title: raspberry apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix apples and raspberries in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, except crust, in a small bowl and sprinkle over fruit.
Mix well and spoon into prepared crust.
Set aside.

title: easy red beans and rice
directions: Brown ground beef and add the Chili-O mix, tomatoes, beans, soup and water.
Slice sausage; add to mixture.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in medium skillet.
Remove 2 tablespoons butter to a small bowl.
Saute onion in skillet until golden.
Add both cans of corn, pimientos, salt and pepper; stir in rice.
Mix well. Pour melted butter across top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until nicely browned.

title: diet barbecue chicken cutlets
directions: Marinate skinless, boneless chicken for several hours or overnight.
Barbecue until done.
(Can bake.)
Low in calories, cholesterol and delicious.
Good for chicken kabobs, too.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water together and set aside.
Mix eggs, margarine, sugar and salt together.
Put both mixtures together and stir in flour.
Set aside in large greased bowl overnight or 6 to 7 hours.
Cover with oiled plastic wrap.
Divide in 3 parts. Roll out 1/3-inch thick circle.
Cut in 8 pie shaped wedges.
Roll up, beginning at large end.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, carrots, oil, eggs and pineapple.
Grease pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Place on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Put toothpicks in tops of balls. Freeze 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter and sugars; mix well.
Stir in egg, vanilla and flour.
Drop by tablespoon.
Press with powdered sugared fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lemony chicken pasta toss
directions: In small bowl, stir together cornstarch, broth, lemon juice, mustard and garlic powder until smooth; set aside.

In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook half of chicken until browned, stirring often. Remove; set aside. Repeat with remaining chicken. Pour off fat. Reduce heat to medium. In same skillet, add reserved cornstarch mixture. Cook mixture until it boils and thickens, stirring constantly. Return chicken to skillet. Heat through, stirring occasionally. Stir in parsley. Toss with spaghetti. If desired, garnish with fresh parsley and lemon. Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix all together. Toss with dressing just before serving.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across grain into thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and add beef.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.
Heat oil in large frying pan on wok.
Add beef, brown well on high heat.
If meat is not tender cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes on low heat.
Add vegetables and cook on high about 10 minutes or until tender crisp.
Mix cornstarch with water, add to pan and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Spread pineapple (not drained) in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Add blueberries and sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar.
Spread dry cake mix over mixture.
Drizzle with oleo.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and nuts and sprinkle over cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 16 to 18. Good warm with ice cream.

title: 7-layer mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth. Add seasoning mix, mixing until well blended. Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate. Layer remaining ingredients over cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate. Serve with tortilla chips. Makes 5 cups.

title: turkey cutlets
directions: Put cutlets in a baking dish; pour wine over and set aside. Dice tomatoes and slice onions.
Remove cutlets from wine. (Reserve wine and add water to equal 1/3 cup.)
In skillet cook cutlets in olive oil.
Turn until brown.
Remove to a warm platter. To drippings add tomatoes, onions, basil and sugar.
Mix cornstarch and wine and add to tomato mixture.
Boil until thick and pour over turkey.

title: amish cabbage with sour cream and bacon
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, then drain and pour nearly all of the fat out of the pan. Set bacon aside.
In the remaining fat, mix cabbage, carrots and potatoes. Sprinkle with flour and add the boiling water, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Cover and cook slowly for 50 minutes. When ready to serve, place cabbage and potatoes in a casserole dish and top with sour cream and crumbled bacon. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew hen without salt.
Skin and pull meat off.
Line large pan with meat.
Mix mushroom soup and celery soup; stir together and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle on stuffing.
Mix cornmeal or regular over top.
Mix chicken broth with milk; pour over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: black bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Sprinkle with coarse pepper just before serving.

title: canned vegetable soup
directions: Cook butter beans about 30 minutes. Mix all ingredients and cook 30 more minutes. Put in jars (hot) and seal. (You can also freeze this.)

title: shrimp salad
directions: Bring water to boil; add shrimp.
Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes. Drain, shell and devein.
In bowl, combine green onion, lemon grass, chili pepper, garlic, lemon juice, fish sauce and oil.
Mix well.
Add shrimp.
Cover and chill.

title: magic chocolate french fudge
directions: Melt chocolate pieces.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Stir thoroughly.
Turn into wax paper lined container.
Press into block 1 inch high.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Turn out; peel off paper.
Cut and store in airtight container.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and the grated onion.
Add a small amount of oil and mix well.
Gradually add alternately the vinegar and oil, ending with oil.
In this way the celery seed will be well mixed in the dressing and it should not separate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla and mix well. Add beaten eggs.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over all.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
When cool you may top with whipped cream (optional).

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, oil, hot chili oil and soy sauce for dressing.

title: fudge bars
directions: In bowl combine oats, B Sugar, Salt & flour add butter mix until crumbly. Stir in pecans & set aside 1 1/2 cup crumbs for topping. Press into 9 x 13 pan.

title: dip pizza
directions: Layer all ingredients on pizza pan.
Use corn chips to dip.

title: carrot pie
directions: Cook carrots covered in water with sugar, vanilla and salt until tender. Remove from heat and drain.
Mash carrots and add the remaining ingredients (except nutmeg) one at a time while mixing.
Pour into homemade pie crust or pre-made pie shell. Sprinkle nutmeg on top of the pie before baking.
(This will make 2 pies.)
Preheat oven to 400° and bake for 50 minutes or until the center is done.

title: party ham-cheese rolls
directions: Mix butter, mustard, Worcestershire and onion.
Cut party rolls in half (whole package at a time), horizontally.
Spread butter mixture on top and bottom of each half.
Put slices of ham and cheese on rolls and put back together.
Put back in aluminum tray and then cut each individual roll.
Heat in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.
(Can freeze before cooking.)

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until smooth.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: governor's salad
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients. Add the peas in a pan and pat down. Mix mayo with sugar; cover the first 4 layers of ingredients. Top with cheese and bacon bits. Best made the day before. Make in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Serves 10 to 15.

title: dot's casserole
directions: Cook ground beef with onion.
Drain grease.
Add cooked bacon, cooked noodles and all other ingredients.
Bake in oven approximately 45 minutes at 300° to 325°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rice, in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan, stirring well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Stir in cooked rice.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir well before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer pan with croutons, then sausage, then cheese (9 x 13-inch), then beat together the rest of the ingredients and pour in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cream-cheesy potatoes
directions: Fry bacon and reserve 2 tablespoons drippings. Cut potatoes into 1-inch cubes and cook
until done. Saute onion in bacon drippings until transparent.
Stir in cheese and sour cream until cheese is melted.
Drain potatoes and sprinkle with 1 or 2 teaspoons seasoned salt.
Pour cheese mixture over potatoes and sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Bake a few minutes.

title: easy taco dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Chill.
Serve with assorted chips or vegetable dippers.

title: biscuit tortoni
directions: Be sure egg whites are at room temperature.
This takes about 1 hour after removing from the refrigerator.

title: apple smiles
directions: Use 2 slices of apples, leaving the skin on.
Spread peanut butter on the inside of the apple, both slices.
Place 5 or 6 mini marshmallows on the peanut butter between the apple slices.
The marshmallows will look like teeth, and the skin will look like lips.
Kids delight in this fun and nutritious treat!

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients by hand (will be stiff).
Roll out on flour.
Fold dough after rolling out into 3 layers.
Cut into noodles (no more than 1/4-inch thick).
Boil chicken in water for 1 hour or until done.
Use broth off of chicken to put noodles in. Pick chicken off the bones.
Put into broth with noodles.
Cook on low together with noodles until noodles are tender.
Serve. Makes 1 gallon.

title: lou's cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into ball.
Cover with additional nuts.
Top with cherry.
Wrap with Saran Wrap. Refrigerate.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Place bottom crust in pie pan; lightly brown in 375 oven. Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared crust.
Cover with top crust.
Crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375 degrees for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: barbecue chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Take chicken off the bone.
Brown chicken pieces in hot oil in large skillet.
Stir in barbecue sauce and water.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes. Stir in rice and corn.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: peach crunch
directions: Place peaches (juice also) in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix flour, sugar and eggs until lumpy.
Spread this mixture over fruit.
Sprinkle top with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
(The flour mixture will not spread out evenly and smoothly but it cooks well.)

title: orange salad
directions: Let
marshmallows melt in hot water.
Add jello and mix well; can
reheat water.
Cool well and add pineapple, grated cheese and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: mother's chicken dressing
directions: Cook chicken and save broth.
Remove chicken from broth and debone.
Crumble corn bread and biscuits (real fine) in large bowl.
Add some broth.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add onions, soups, milk, melted margarine, sage, pepper and salt.
(mixture needs to be real soupy.)
Pour in a large roasting pan; add chicken pieces.
Cook at 350° for about an hour or longer.
Insert knife in the center to test for doneness.
Use remaining chicken for Giblet Gravy.
Canned chicken broth may be used, if needed.

title: slush
directions: Boil the sugar and water for 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in container and freeze.
Serve with 7-Up or ginger ale.
Great summer drink!

title: easy salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and Jell-O, then add crushed pineapple, mandarin oranges and cottage cheese.
Add cherries for color.

title: delicious apple pie
directions: Butter baking dish.
Sprinkle apples with lemon juice, if desired.
Cut bread into finger size lengths and lattice over sliced apples.
Mix together sugar, flour, egg and butter.
Pour over bread, covering each piece well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: italian slaw
directions: Boil oil, vinegar, sugar, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Pour over cabbage and onions.
Cover and refrigerate.
Toss occasionally for 12 hours.
Serve.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Grease 13 x 9 pan. Line pan with boneless chicken breasts. Cover with shaved ham. Place slices of Swiss cheese over ham. Mix cream of chicken soup with water and spread over cheese. Combine melted butter with stuffing mix. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°. Remove foil last 15 minutes.

title: mock raspberry jam
directions: Cook tomatoes and sugar 15 minutes.
Add the jellos.
Cook 10 minutes.
Skim top and pour into jars.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 12 x 8-inch shallow baking dish.
Discard outer leaves from cabbage.
Wash head of cabbage. Cut into 1-inch wedges.
Pour 1 cup water in large skillet and bring to boiling.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and the cabbage.
Cook over medium heat, covered, 10 minutes.
Drain well.

title: split pea soup
directions: Rinse
split
peas several times.
Combine all ingredients
in a
large
saucepan or Dutch oven.
Cover with water. Cook
on slow burner until peas melt to a smooth consistency. Add more water if necessary.
Good served with French bread.

title: squash pie
directions: Cook squash until tender and water evaporates.
Measure out 2 cups squash.
Add margarine while squash is hot; add other ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Best when completely cool!!

title: hot taco dip
directions: Cube up all your cheeses.
Brown hamburger.
Combine all in a crock-pot until melted.
Serve with chips.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place drained asparagus on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix mushroom soup, eggs and almonds together.
Spread over the top of asparagus.
Cook for 30 minutes at 400° in oven.
Serves 4 people.

title: lemon shrimp rounds
directions: In a medium mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in lemon juice. Stir in shrimp, onion, horseradish and pepper. Chill. Serve with Melba toast.

title: creamy potatoes and franks
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Blend in flour, onion, salt, mustard and garlic salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Stir in cheese, potatoes and wieners.
Spoon mixture into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and let cool to a syrupy stage. Add strawberries (thawed), cake and Cool Whip.
Pour into 8 x 13-inch baking dish and chill.
Cut in squares.
Top with a dab of Cool Whip and a berry.

title: chicken sauté bourguignon
directions: Flatten chicken breasts between waxed paper to 1/4-inch thickness.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cut into quarters.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in large heavy skillet over medium heat. Cook chicken 5 minutes or until no longer pink and transfer to platter.
Add mushrooms to skillet and cook 2 minutes.
Add onions, shallots, bay leaf, garlic and thyme.
Cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Sprinkle in flour.
Stir in broth and wine.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Whisk in remaining butter.
Add chicken; heat through. Add salt and pepper.
Remove bay leaf.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine ingredients. Turn into unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes; reduce heat and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 9 1/2-inch Pyrex pie plate in oven.
In mixing bowl, combine meal, flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add enough hot water to mix ingredients together. Add egg and beat well.
Add milk.
Pour into pie plate with margarine.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mound cake
directions: Mix by instructions on box.
Bake in two 9-inch cake pans. Turn out on rack to cool.
Slice each layer in two, giving you 4 layers.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Brown meat; add salsa, corn, salad dressing and chili powder. Layer in casserole the meat, cheese and crushed chips, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken or turkey pot pie
directions: Cook vegetables together until tender; discard onion and celery.
Mix vegetables, meat and soup together in a bowl.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with biscuits or homemade dough and bake at 425° until golden brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ronnie's delight
directions: Take cookies (any favorite) and layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Layer 1/2 Cool Whip, then another layer of cookies, then remaining Cool Whip.
Set overnight.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together; pour into a 9 x 13-inch oblong baking dish.
Top with crushed potato chips and 1/4 cup of pecans.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Spread graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Cover with mixed pudding.
Chill.
Layer bananas, then Cool Whip followed by strawberries and pineapple. Sprinkle coconut on top.
Refrigerate. Makes 8 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring margarine and tomato juice to a boil in large saucepan. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Discard bay leaves.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: tomato shrimp gumbo
directions: Put oil in 3 quart pot.
Clean and devein shrimp.
When oil is hot, add shrimp and toss for 1 minute.
Remove and add onions, red pepper and garlic.
Cook until soft.
Sprinkle on flour
and toss.
Add stock, salt, pepper, tomatoes (cut up), okra and
rice. Make
a
paste
of
the file and 1 tablespoon water and add.
Put shrimp back into pot, turn off heat; ready to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crazy 'bout snickers bars
directions: Chop 4 squares of chocolate; set aside.
Mix melted margarine with cookie crumbs.
Press into bottom of foil-lined 9-inch square pan.
Top with caramel topping.

title: brownies
directions: Melt oleo; add cocoa.
Cream sugar into mixture.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Bake in pan sized according to thickness desired.
Be sure to melt cocoa, oleo and sugar in saucepan. This cannot be dry mixed.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add milk and egg yolks that have been beaten or mixed.
Cook until you have desired thickness.
Add vanilla and let cool.
Pour over layered bananas and wafers.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and put on top of pudding and brown in oven.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; make sure "all" liquid is out of it.
Mix "all" ingredients together.
Best if refrigerated for a few hours before serving.
Can be served with fresh veggies.
Serves a large group. Cut in half for smaller group.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and chocolate in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove and stir in sugar; cool to room temperature.
Stir in eggs and vanilla, then flour and nuts.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square baking pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Allow to stand 5 to 10 minutes, then spread melted chocolate chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini, pineapple, vanilla and nuts. Beat lightly and well.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Mix to blend.
Put into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: ginger hearts with raspberry filling
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour, cloves and cinnamon.
Roll out and cut into heart shapes.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 9 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix butter, cheese, pepper and salt with an electric mixer. Add flour and mix well.

title: strawberry truffle
directions: Break cake into small pieces in a deep dish.
Mix dry jello and frozen strawberries together.
Pour over cake.
Put sliced bananas over mixture.
Mix pudding with 2% milk as directed and pour over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in buttered pie plate 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple to a boil.
Add jello to dissolve.
Let cool. Then add buttermilk.
Let cool until slightly thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix and let congeal.

title: old fashioned plain cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until center springs back when pressed.

title: grape punch
directions: Use half of the pineapple juice and make ice cubes or a ring. Mix rest of the ingredients.
Chill until serving time, then add 7-Up.

title: chuck wagon mac
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper in large skillet.
Pour off fat. Stir in tomato sauce and corn; simmer.
Cook macaroni and cheese according to package directions, adding enclosed packet, margarine and milk.
Stir macaroni mixture into meat mixture until mixed well.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° until casserole bubbles and cheese is melted, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in jar and shake well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: christmas rocks
directions: Mix all dried fruit and nuts in flour.
Then mix together with eggs, sugar, cinnamon and margarine.
Add drained cherries and soda.
Add some juice of red cherries, this adds taste and color.
Bake 350° for 12-15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: blueberry fritters
directions: Combine flour and blueberries; toss lightly and set aside. Combine next 4 ingredients in mixing bowl; mix well.
Combine egg and milk.
Gradually add milk mixture to flour mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together.
Pour in long pan.
Freeze.
This can be frozen to have later.

title: mini peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine and sugar.
Roll in small balls. Chill in freezer 20 minutes.
Dip in melted white chocolate. Place dipped eggs on waxed paper.
Good any time.

title: potato chowder
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Saute until tender.
Add potatoes, water, pepper, paprika and bouillon cubes.
Cover.
Simmer 10 to 20 minutes until potatoes are done.
Combine flour and a small amount of water (1/4 cup) into a paste.
Add to potato soup.
Add milk and cook until thickened. Stir constantly.

title: holiday cider
directions: In a crock-pot warm Kool-Aid and red hots.
Serve warm. Tastes like apple cider!
Extremely easy!!!

title: peach carrot cake
directions: Drain peaches well and crush 1 cup with fork in strainer. Combine peaches with all remaining ingredients.
Spoon into two greased 8-inch square pans.
Bake in 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes. Cool on wire racks.

title: butterscotch cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in a bowl and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
In a small bowl, mix together remaining 3 ingredients.
Pour over batter in pan.
Cut in with knife and swirl.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, cream butter and sugars together. Add eggs and vanilla and mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix until blended. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat for about 10 minutes. Strain and serve hot.

title: cream of broccoli crab soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; set aside.
In a large pan, saute onion in butter; blend in flour.
Add milk and half and half slowly.
Cook until thickened and smooth.
Dissolve bouillon in the hot mixture.
Add seasonings, crab and broccoli. Heat thoroughly and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all together by hand.
Save a small piece of dough for the top to criss-cross.
Put dough in oblong pan; pat in with hands. Spread your choice of filling.
Can use two different kinds on top. Then roll dough that was saved in pencil thick strips to criss-cross on top of filling.
Bake at 300° for one hour.
You may use 2 square pans instead of oblong shape if desired.

title: joyce's poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix everything together, except oil and poppy seed.
With electric mixer, slowly pour in salad oil.
Add poppy seed and continue to beat until well mixed.
Store in tight container in refrigerator.

title: all purpose punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken in salad oil.
Remove chicken and saute onions and celery until tender.
Add remaining ingredients to vegetables. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Skim off excess fat.
Place chicken in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Pour sauce over.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and trim squash.
Cook until tender.
Drain in colander. Melt oleo in pot that squash was cooked in.
Saute onions in oleo until tender.
Add squash, egg, soup, salt and pepper.
Pour in a casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer each ingredient, putting crackers next to last and cover with the mayonnaise.
Garnish with cucumbers, radishes and black olives.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter, powdered sugar & rice krispies, form into balls and place on wax paper.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter, egg yolks and sugar.
Add milk and mashed bananas.
Mix gradually.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Beat well.
Add nuts and raisins mixed with a little flour.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour in 2 bread pans, greased and floured. Let stand 15 minutes.
Bake 1 hour.
Melt butter on top and rub cinnamon on top.

title: hummus dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chop in food processor.
If too thick, add a little more lemon juice.
Excellent Arabic dish. This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix pudding and 2 cups milk.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Pet milk and mix well.
Add fruit of your choice.
Place in churn when all mixed together and churn until firm.

title: company potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place potatoes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in large bowl the next 6 ingredients; pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with corn flakes and margarine mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: the best brownies
directions: Mix vegetable oil or melted butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add baking powder, salt and cocoa; mix again until smooth.
Add flour.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Pour into a large cookie sheet (greased).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone; cut into bite size pieces. Blend cream cheese with milk.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all ingredients except seasoned stuffing mix which is to be sprinkled over top.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 or 3 casseroles.
May be frozen, cooked or uncooked.

title: buttermilk sherbet
directions: Mix buttermilk, 2/3 of the sugar, salt, pineapple and vanilla.
Freeze until half frozen.
Beat well.
Beat the egg white until stiff; add remaining sugar.
Fold into the pineapple mixture and return to freezer and freeze until ready to eat.

title: calzones
directions: Roll out 1 dough onto cookie sheet.
Mix Ricotta cheese, egg, spices and garlic.
Spread over bottom crust.
Sprinkle the three types of shredded cheese over this.
Top with the rest of the dough, sealing the edges.
Bake until golden brown, 20 to 30 minutes, at 350°.
Serve plain or with spaghetti sauce and meat.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; pack firmly into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Yield:
6 servings.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into equal portions.
Mix together flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Coat steak with this flour mixture.
Brown steak in half of the butter and oil.
Put steak in crock-pot.
Heat remaining butter and oil and saute onion, carrots and celery, until onion is transparent.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar.
Cook for three minutes.
Pour veggies over meat with oil liquid and cook for 6 to 8 hours on low setting.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well.
Alternate flour and milk.
Add flavorings.
Mix well. Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast and egg. Gradually stir in flour to form soft dough.
Beat vigorously. Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine ground cranberries, ground orange and sugar.
Cover and chill one hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, margarine and evaporated milk. Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage (238°) for about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, stirring well, then add nuts, vanilla and marshmallow cream, beating until smooth.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: cheese torte
directions: Line pan with crust.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter; add soup, milk, mushrooms, pimiento and basil.
Place half the noodles in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with half each of mushroom sauce, cottage cheese, chicken and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: fabulous avocado dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and serve with corn chips.

title: golden wedding punch
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Chill and pour over ring mold in punch bowl.
Just before serving, float sherbet.
Makes 7 gallons. Serves 100.

title: pumpkin-oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix all other ingredients in a blender.
Combine with dry ingredients and stir just to mix.

title: frozen salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Set aside. Mix strawberries, pineapple and nuts.
Spoon into creamed mixture, then fold in either the bananas or peaches.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan or two smaller dishes.
Freeze.

title: tic-tac-toe
directions: Melt over hot water the butterscotch morsels.
Place noodles and peanuts in a bowl.
Add melted butterscotch and stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Chill until firm. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chocolate fudge roll cookie
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
When melted, add sweetened condensed milk and nuts.
Stir until smooth; set aside to cool.
Mix together in bowl the margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla; stir until smooth.
Add flour and baking powder.
You may need to add more flour if dough is too sticky.
Separate into fourths.
Shape into rectangle, then roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cover with chocolate filling and roll up.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Crush wafers; mix with milk and syrup.
Let warm to room temperature.
In a separate bowl, mix fruits and nuts.
Mix well with wafers.
Pack tightly in a buttered pan that can be put in oven.
Put into refrigerator overnight.
Next day, preheat oven to 400° for 15 minutes.
Then turn oven off and place cake in oven about 15 minutes.
Run knife around edge of pan and turn cake out onto double layer of foil.
Wrap and keep in refrigerator.

title: hearty vegetable beef soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low for 12 to 24 hours or high 4 to 6 hours.

title: myrtle's cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Butter sides of casserole dish.
Pour vegetable mixture into dish.
Mix 1 cup cracker crumbs with 3/4 cup butter.
Sprinkle over mixture and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add butter.
Chop flour and butter until it looks like cornmeal.
Beat sour cream, egg and milk; fold into dry ingredients.
Mix well. Add raisins.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.
Pour into container and refrigerate.
It thickens as it cools.
Makes 1 1/2 cups milk (equal to 14 ounce can).
Use in any recipe calling for condensed milk.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a big bowl.
Add liquids and eggs. Refrigerate overnight; bake for 15 to 18 minutes at 400°.
Can be made up a few at a time.
Will last up to 6 weeks in refrigerator. (Makes a big batch; you may want to cut in half.)

title: hungarian kifle cookies
directions: Mix cheese and butter well.
Add flour; mix until it stays in a ball.
Let stand until well chilled in refrigerator.
Roll out thin; cut into 2-inch squares.
Fill with dots of jam.
Fold in 2 corners to make crescents.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Can be frozen raw or baked until needed.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: seasoned baked potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes and place in casserole dish. Sprinkle generously with seasoned salt.
Cut up oleo over potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Potatoes may need to be turned after 45 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in butter in large saucepan until tender, 20 minutes.
Stir in next four seasonings and remove from heat.
Stir together eggs and cheese in large bowl and add vegetable mixture.

title: mashed potatoes, lemon and caper style
directions: Boil potatoes until done in your usual manner. Drain, then mash potatoes.

title: cheese pound cake
directions: Mix
cheese, sugar and margarine and beat until creamy. Add vanilla
and
sour	cream.	Blend.	Add
flour
and blend together.
Pour batter into greased Bundt pan.
Do not preheat oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: microwave s'mores
directions: For each serving, place 4 squares of a chocolate bar and 1 marshmallow on a graham crackers.
Microwave on High power 15 to 20 seconds or until marshmallow puffs.
Top with second graham cracker.
Eat like a sandwich!

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, bacon and raisins.
Set aside. Combine sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar to make a dressing.
Pour over and mix into broccoli mixture.

title: lemon creme bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Gradually stir in flour until well blended.
Pat in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 235° for 15 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cut extra potatoes up and cook.
Drain and add to soup.
Melt margarine first and start cooking on high, then turn on low and stir often.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg, vanilla and extract.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Roll dough on floured board.
Cut into assorted shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown 7 to 8 minutes.

title: sweet crisp pickles
directions: Soak for 24 hours.
Slice cucumbers, lime and water.
Wash in cold water several times.
Soak 3 hours in clear cold water.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Drain strawberries.
Add Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill until firm.
You can substitute strawberries with 1 can crushed pineapple (drained) and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Makes 2 pies. Freezes well.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Fill quart jar with cucumbers. Add the pickle spice, salt, alum and vinegar. Fill jar the rest of the way with hot water and seal. After 8 weeks, put 1 cup sugar per jar.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cook peppers and onions in part of the margarine with sugar until tender.
Add drained tomatoes.
Line bottom of baking dish with saltine crackers.
Place tomato mixture on saltines, alternating layers.
Top with shredded cheese, then cover well with crushed buttered saltines. Bake at 350° until top lightly browns.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Mix butter.
Add cocoa and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients in order given.
Stir (do not beat).
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not remove from pan.

title: lamb chop skillet
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper on both sides.
Add wine, water and bouillon cube.
Simmer 1/2 hour, covered.

title: vegetable pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, garlic, dill and salt; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly. Chill several hours or overnight.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and mayonnaise until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables. Makes 2 cups.

title: marianne's muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spoon into greased muffins and bake at 200°C for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: belgian beef stew
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper. Add chuck to coat; set aside.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in 4-quart Dutch oven.
Saute onion and garlic until tender; remove from pan.
Heat remaining oil and add chuck.
Brown well on all sides.
Return onion and garlic to pan, along with beer, soy sauce, Worcestershire, steak sauce, bay leaves and thyme.
Mix well. Bring mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: beet-orange-apple salad
directions: Coarsely shred beet greens to measure 2 cups; set aside.
Leave root and 1-inch of stem on 2 beets, reserving remaining beets for another time.
Scrub with a brush and set aside.
Place beets in a small saucepan and add water to cover and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain and let cool.
Trim off beet stems and roots and rub off skins.
Cut each beet into 8 wedges.
Set aside.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: To cake mix, add eggs.
Bake in 4 layers.
Mix and spread next 3 ingredients between layers.
Reserve 1/3 of filling for icing. To this add Cool Whip.
Mix together and cover top and sides of cake.
Cover and store in refrigerator for 3 days before cutting.

title: easy refrigerator roll dough(these are reid's favorite rolls.)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixer bowl.
Add sugar, salt, egg, shortening and 1 cup of the flour.
(If using self-rising flour, omit salt.)
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour; continue stirring until smooth.
Scrape batter from side of bowl.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 30 minutes.
Stir down batter.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups, filling each about 1/2 full.
Let rise until batter reaches tops of cups, 20 to 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Let stand overnight.
Before serving, add bananas and grapes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Melt butter.
Add with egg to dry ingredients and add applesauce.
Beat well.
Pour into greased tube cake pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Place sugars, butter, eggs and vanilla in bowl.
Beat on medium for 30 seconds.
Stop and scrape bowl.
Beat on high for 30 more seconds.

title: corn and tamales
directions: In
a
lightly greased 2-quart casserole, layer half of the ingredients listed.
Repeat with other half.
If desired, salt and pepper to taste between layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: eggplant burgers
directions: Cut unpeeled eggplant into cubes and steam until tender; drain.
Put in mixing bowl and add all ingredients, except flour. Sprinkle your hands with flour and shape mixture into patties. Fry in hot oil.
Serve hot.

title: coconut frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; blend in sugar, milk and extract.
Fold in whipped topping and coconut.
Makes about 4 cups, enough to frost 9 x 13-inch or two 8-inch cakes.
Store frosting in refrigerator.

title: french fried onions
directions: Peel onion.
Cut in thin slices and separate into rings.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Dip each ring into batter and drop into hot grease.
Fry about 3 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Drain.

title: polka dot cake
directions: Mix chopped dates and hot water; set aside to cool.
Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with date mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and 1/2 cup chips.
Spread batter in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with rest of chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla, flour, nuts and salt.
Work together with hands.
Form into 1 inch balls. Flatten balls slightly.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: coconut impossible pie
directions: Mix all together and place in a 10-inch pie dish, greased with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
In 40 minutes, check. If pie is brown on top, pie is done.

title: easy apple dumplings
directions: Divide biscuits in half to make 20 rounds.
Quarter apple, then cut quarters into five bite-size pieces (to make 20 pieces of apples). Put a piece of apple into each round and arrange "dumplings" in a baking dish.
Bring water, butter and sugar to a boil and pour over dumplings.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: marinated salad
directions: Drain vegetables and combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix with next 5.
Heat to boiling and refrigerate overnight.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Fry onion and ground beef in skillet and brown slightly.
Add rest of ingredients in layers.
Heat on top of stove until it steams, then place in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Dip spoon straight down to the bottom so as to serve in layers.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry-lined pie pan.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour cream mixture into pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 main dish servings; 8 appetizer servings.

title: potato topped casserole
directions: Brown onion and meat.
Season and add corn.
Stir.
Cover and simmer while potatoes cook.
Boil potatoes for creaming.
Drain. Add butter and milk, then cream. Drain meat mixture and put in casserole dish. Cover with the mashed potatoes and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Place under broiler just long enough for cheese to melt.
(May also use instant potatoes.)

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Mix all ingredients except crackers and margarine.
Pour into a 1-quart buttered casserole. Mix crackers with melted margarine.
Put on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients; add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Remove from mixer; stir in boiling water.
Pour into baking pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350°.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Separate chicken from broth and set aside to cool.
Add all ingredients except noodles to broth until tender.
Debone chicken; cut into small pieces and add to mixture. Add noodles and cook until tender.
Set aside five minutes and serve.

title: cold russian soup
directions: Chop fine cucumbers, onions, dill, parsley and pickles.
Add to mix, buttermilk, yogurt and dash of Tabasco.
Garnish with shrimp.

title: curried chicken sandwiches
directions: Cook chicken breasts; add mayonnaise to moisten. Add 1 tablespoon of curry powder (more or less) for taste.
Chop dates and pecans fine. Add to mixture.

title: bosworth zucchini
directions: Slice squash and onion and mix with tomatoes in a saucepan. Cook covered until done.
Top with grated cheese.

title: cherry yum yum desert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine together.
Press on the bottom of an oblong glass casserole dish.
Mix with and electric mixer, the softened cream cheese, condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla extract together until creamy.
Pour over crust in casserole dish.
Spread evenly and top with the can of cherry pie filling.
Chill well before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with 1 cup corn flake crumbs mixed with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cobb salad with tortellini
directions: Cook tortellini in boiling water for ten minutes.
Drain and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and marinate for one hour before serving.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Skin, bone and cube chicken breasts.
Prepare mushrooms. Drain bamboo shoots and water chestnuts.
Slice onion and celery into thin pieces.
